WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:34.460 --> 00:00:36.635
﻿Plasma Youth Sports Games
with Unsuccess of the champion,

00:00:36.722 --> 00:00:39.209
would like to thank Slaven Bilić
for stepping in as the host.

00:00:39.285 --> 00:00:42.436
Bilić is one of the first sponsors,
ambassador and is our biggest promoter.

00:00:42.594 --> 00:00:45.819
He used his life and sports experience
in order to prepare high-quality content

00:00:45.979 --> 00:00:48.019
with his guests for all generations.
Thanks, Nane!

00:00:51.220 --> 00:00:54.978
It's easy now, after 13 years, to talk about
that when all of it’s well known to you.

00:00:55.155 --> 00:01:01.853
Do you remember the moment when you
came to the locker room for the first time

00:01:02.142 --> 00:01:05.933
at the Santiago Bernabeu Stadium?
I never played for Real Madrid,

00:01:06.064 --> 00:01:08.162
not did I work there as a coach.

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:13.831
However, the late Radomir Antić,
who was the coach of Atletico,

00:01:13.999 --> 00:01:19.198
Real and Barcelona, said that the atmosphere
at Bernabeu simply "swallows" you.

00:01:19.339 --> 00:01:24.386
Do you remember the moment when you
first came? -Of course I remember.

00:01:24.644 --> 00:01:29.058
I felt that atmosphere in the stadium
when we played against Tottenham

00:01:29.219 --> 00:01:31.815
in the quarter-finals
of the Champions League.

00:01:32.180 --> 00:01:35.220
During the warm-up, while Čarli
and I were warming up,

00:01:35.350 --> 00:01:37.790
at one moment I approached him
and told him that I felt

00:01:37.992 --> 00:01:40.421
as if the crowd was right
on top of my head.

00:01:40.624 --> 00:01:43.024
I looked around and couldn't
believe where I was.

00:01:43.162 --> 00:01:46.366
It’s an unbelievable feeling.
So I can understand the teams

00:01:46.527 --> 00:01:49.663
that come to play against Real.
And how hard it’s and what respect

00:01:49.850 --> 00:01:52.610
they have for Real
when they play against it.

00:01:52.811 --> 00:01:57.731
And that’s the difference that Real
has compared to other clubs.

00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:03.445
Despite the fact that Real's fans
aren't known for being ultra loud.

00:02:03.723 --> 00:02:08.882
That's right, but when necessary,
they know how to be. They're more like...

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:12.636
They’re good, they’re not ultra loud,
except when playing matches

00:02:12.748 --> 00:02:15.530
against strong opponents.
Then their support is phenomenal.

00:02:15.620 --> 00:02:17.820
As if they’re "pushing the bus".
-That's right.

00:02:18.605 --> 00:02:23.379
But that experience at
the Bernabeu is truly incredible.

00:02:23.542 --> 00:02:26.559
That feeling of awe is hard to describe.

00:02:26.695 --> 00:02:33.324
It’s hard to explain it until
you walk out to play on the pitch.

00:02:33.643 --> 00:02:37.483
That feeling is really something special.

00:02:37.988 --> 00:02:42.910
And whether I remember the moments
when I came for the first time.

00:02:43.155 --> 00:02:47.207
On the first day, I did the medical check up
and everything that was necessary.

00:02:47.362 --> 00:02:51.168
And I went to the stadium
so I could be presented.

00:02:52.796 --> 00:02:56.957
The same afternoon we had training,
I entered the Valdebebas camp.

00:02:57.207 --> 00:03:02.902
Iker Casillas was the first to meet me
outside locker room and welcomed me.

00:03:03.161 --> 00:03:07.637
He told me to feel at home and
feel free to say whatever I needed.

00:03:07.792 --> 00:03:10.027
We had the usual conversation.

00:03:10.276 --> 00:03:15.293
Then, when I entered the locker room,
I saw the best players in the world.

00:03:15.364 --> 00:03:20.152
My God. -Cristiano, Karim,
Higuain, Xabi Alonso.

00:03:20.385 --> 00:03:23.137
I found Cristian while he was
on the massage table,

00:03:23.231 --> 00:03:25.730
and he told me the following:
"Finally, you’ve arrived".

00:03:25.832 --> 00:03:28.472
Because the whole procedure
for my transfer took two months.

00:03:28.696 --> 00:03:34.840
I walked in among the best players
in the world. -But you still thought...

00:03:35.083 --> 00:03:38.683
I came to impose myself...
-You knew you belonged there.

00:03:39.180 --> 00:03:46.766
... and to prove I didn't come by accident.
So I was just thinking about that.

00:03:49.983 --> 00:03:55.233
However, you didn’t do preseason with
them because of the transfer procedure.

00:03:56.420 --> 00:04:02.100
That's why your play wasn't
great at the very beginning.

00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:10.620
In those moments,
while all of that was happening...

00:04:11.020 --> 00:04:16.220
Especially because you’re not
the type who attracts attention

00:04:16.460 --> 00:04:19.980
with things happening off the pitch.

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:24.140
With some trendy bag when arriving
for training, designer shoes,

00:04:24.340 --> 00:04:27.220
or maybe a hairstyle.
Giving interviews.

00:04:27.460 --> 00:04:30.380
You’re one of those players
who show everything on the pitch.

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:34.940
However, at that moment you didn’t
have many chances on the pitch,

00:04:35.180 --> 00:04:40.017
except in training. But in matches
you didn’t have them.

00:04:40.216 --> 00:04:42.963
It's easy to talk about it now
after everything has passed,

00:04:43.094 --> 00:04:46.180
but people need to know that in Real
they don't suffer oscillations in the game.

00:04:46.952 --> 00:04:50.035
It’s a club where they call you out
immediately after bad games.

00:04:50.141 --> 00:04:52.604
In those moments, did you regret
not moving to Chelsea

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:54.549
or perhaps staying in Tottenham?

00:04:54.671 --> 00:04:59.331
Or are you someone who always
fights for his place in the team?

00:04:59.700 --> 00:05:06.180
Not for a moment did I regret.
I was happy to come to such a club.

00:05:06.540 --> 00:05:11.340
That I could train with those players.
To be in such a club.

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:17.420
Right away during training
I felt that I belonged there.

00:05:17.660 --> 00:05:22.540
There I realized that is it. I also
played against some of those players

00:05:22.780 --> 00:05:26.860
and felt I during the matches
that I could play them.

00:05:27.820 --> 00:05:30.580
I knew from the first moment
that I belonged there

00:05:30.860 --> 00:05:34.220
and I never doubted
that I would not succeed.

00:05:34.860 --> 00:05:39.020
No matter how hard it was
in the beginning, and regardless

00:05:39.135 --> 00:05:41.681
of the fact that sometimes
I played and sometimes I didn't.

00:05:41.918 --> 00:05:46.550
That year Real didn’t have a good start.
-Mourinho was the coach? -Yes, he was.

00:05:46.713 --> 00:05:49.873
He was the most deserving
for me coming to Real.

00:05:49.996 --> 00:05:53.236
If he hadn’t been the coach
I might never have come to Real.

00:05:53.374 --> 00:05:56.385
He wasn’t looking for a midfielder,
he was looking for Luka Modrić.

00:05:56.531 --> 00:05:58.731
He was looking for me
and no one else.

00:05:58.815 --> 00:06:02.518
During that period
of negotiations,

00:06:02.726 --> 00:06:05.446
the club offered him
various other players,

00:06:05.591 --> 00:06:08.391
because they thought
my transfer wouldn’t happen.

00:06:08.593 --> 00:06:16.073
I want to thank the president of Tottenham
because he kept his promise.

00:06:16.234 --> 00:06:21.573
Although those months were painful
for me, I also felt a lot of stress.

00:06:21.940 --> 00:06:26.475
I didn't play games, and I didn't even know
if my transfer to Real would happen.

00:06:27.020 --> 00:06:30.497
In the end, the Tottenham
president kept his promise,

00:06:30.643 --> 00:06:32.786
but negotiating with him
was really difficult.

00:06:32.897 --> 00:06:38.903
Something similar happened to Keane...
-And with Bale, Keane, Berbatov.

00:06:39.208 --> 00:06:44.115
A lot of players went through
a similar situation.

00:06:44.140 --> 00:06:47.020
Because of that situation,
at one point Real

00:06:47.220 --> 00:06:50.580
started thinking about other players
like Silva, Mata, Cazorla.

00:06:50.820 --> 00:06:54.460
However, at that moment
Mourinho was respected,

00:06:54.700 --> 00:06:59.260
and president Florentino
liked him and still does.

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:03.380
He also won the championship?
-He won the title with a record number

00:07:03.580 --> 00:07:07.300
of points. Mourinho said:
"Either Luka or nobody."

00:07:07.580 --> 00:07:11.540
And that made the difference. He could
have said he didn’t want to wait,

00:07:11.820 --> 00:07:16.580
but he still decided on me.
Because of that I’m very grateful.

00:07:17.460 --> 00:07:20.700
We still sometimes talk on the phone.
I'm always happy to see him.

00:07:20.900 --> 00:07:26.820
I regret that I didn't have the chance
to work with him more than one year.

00:07:27.220 --> 00:07:31.380
Were you angry at him because at first
you didn’t play in the starting eleven?

00:07:31.533 --> 00:07:37.853
I wasn't angry. He talked to me a lot
and told me to be patient.

00:07:38.300 --> 00:07:45.447
After a period when I would play
a match, in my opinion well.

00:07:45.634 --> 00:07:49.820
However, after 60 or 55 minutes
he would substitute me.

00:07:50.060 --> 00:07:53.300
In one match, after only
the first half, I had to come off.

00:07:53.500 --> 00:07:56.700
In some later matches
I only got 10 minutes.

00:07:56.940 --> 00:08:04.340
At one point it became
frustrating for me.

00:08:04.540 --> 00:08:07.100
Because I knew I was playing well.

00:08:07.340 --> 00:08:11.156
I felt through the matches
that I was playing well.

00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:18.433
At that moment, the atmosphere
in the club wasn’t the best either.

00:08:18.941 --> 00:08:25.832
As much as I didn't understand
Spanish, I could feel it.

00:08:28.180 --> 00:08:33.100
Despite the fact that he didn't talk
to me, his assistants did talk.

00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:37.500
Rui Faria, after a match we played
against Deportivo La Coruna,

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:42.340
in which I was substituted
in the 55th or 60th minute.

00:08:42.780 --> 00:08:49.777
The next day he came to check on me.
Do I need anything, how I feel.

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:54.940
If anything bothered me, etc.
At that moment, I told him everything

00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:59.260
that was bothering me. Because
I knew he would tell Mourinho.

00:08:59.580 --> 00:09:05.620
On that occasion I told him everything.
I told him: "Let me play four or

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:12.780
five games in a row, and if I don't do
what is expected, I will never complain.

00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:16.300
I only ask for this to have continuity.
If I don’t meet your conditions,

00:09:16.540 --> 00:09:21.380
you can do whatever you want."
He then told me: "Don't worry,

00:09:21.620 --> 00:09:25.945
we're more than satisfied with you.
Whenever you play, we're satisfied.

00:09:26.163 --> 00:09:31.973
Don't worry, your time will come."
After that, the situation improved.

00:09:33.027 --> 00:09:40.406
This conversation happened sometime
in February, before the Champions League

00:09:40.565 --> 00:09:43.828
match against Manchester.
-That was the match. -After that goal.

00:09:44.005 --> 00:09:51.685
Did my conversation and confidence help?
Confidence and belief in myself when I said

00:09:51.980 --> 00:09:56.740
I wanted to play several matches in a row
so I could show what kind of player I am.

00:09:56.940 --> 00:10:01.140
I came to play. After that talk,
maybe my status changed,

00:10:01.340 --> 00:10:05.540
and I started getting more minutes. After
that came the match against Manchester.

00:10:05.780 --> 00:10:08.740
Which was crucial for me. -When
Nani got sent off and you scored.

00:10:08.980 --> 00:10:14.020
I shouldn't have even entered the game.
Kaká came on if I’m not mistaken.

00:10:14.300 --> 00:10:17.303
I almost entered the pitch
without a substitution made.

00:10:17.533 --> 00:10:20.201
I couldn't wait for Mourinho
to invite me into the game.

00:10:20.342 --> 00:10:23.061
After that he called me, I came in,
and what happened, happened.

00:10:23.204 --> 00:10:25.936
After that match, the others
and even the journalists...

00:10:26.075 --> 00:10:28.897
After that match everything
turned around. -That's right.

00:10:29.106 --> 00:10:34.478
It would probably happen later,
but that match was...

00:10:34.822 --> 00:10:38.587
That’s exactly what I wanted to say.

00:10:38.981 --> 00:10:44.021
Of course, even great players
need that factor of luck

00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:49.380
for things to turn their way,
to score a goal, etc.

00:10:49.980 --> 00:10:53.321
The same would happen after seven,
fifteen days or three weeks after that.

00:10:53.492 --> 00:10:57.118
There is no doubt about that.
After that, the flow begins.

00:10:58.324 --> 00:11:03.610
The following year,
Carlo Ancelotti came as coach

00:11:03.832 --> 00:11:09.711
and you won La Decima,
which you say is special.

00:11:10.260 --> 00:11:16.180
A special Champions League
out of all six I’ve won.

00:11:16.420 --> 00:11:20.700
Because it was the tenth,
and I really love the number ten.

00:11:22.740 --> 00:11:26.180
You played Atletico Madrid.
-Yes, against Atletico.

00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:32.540
In the 90th minute you assisted Ramos.
-I think it was the 93rd minute.

00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:37.100
It was truly incredible.

00:11:37.380 --> 00:11:41.540
And that was a good example
of what kind of club Real is,

00:11:41.780 --> 00:11:46.700
that they never give up on winning.
Regardless of problems,

00:11:47.020 --> 00:11:51.807
players always believe
they can do something.

00:11:52.478 --> 00:11:57.178
At that moment, that match
was the perfect example,

00:11:57.599 --> 00:12:01.479
and earlier in Real’s history
there were many similar matches.

00:12:01.740 --> 00:12:10.740
How come you didn't stop then?
It’s like you became addicted to winning.

00:12:11.060 --> 00:12:14.740
After winning the title,
you didn't stop there.

00:12:15.020 --> 00:12:21.740
You just kept going further and further.
As a team you became obsessed.

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:26.580
You won the Champions League six times.
You beat Atletico twice, Liverpool twice.

00:12:26.780 --> 00:12:30.820
Then Juventus and Borussia Dortmund.
-That's right. -You have won six times.

00:12:31.020 --> 00:12:34.540
Yes, that's incredible.
-It was like you pushed each other.

00:12:34.780 --> 00:12:39.180
We were hungry for success.
Real simply gives you that.

00:12:39.340 --> 00:12:44.300
When we won the 10th Champions League,
and they start talking about the 11th.

00:12:44.620 --> 00:12:48.180
You think, we just won the 10th,
let us enjoy it a little.

00:12:48.420 --> 00:12:56.140
A player at Real has no time to enjoy it,
because they are asking for the next.

00:12:56.300 --> 00:13:00.140
Right away they begin talking
about the next Champions League,

00:13:00.340 --> 00:13:03.620
because it’s something special
for them. -That’s Real. -Exactly.

00:13:03.742 --> 00:13:06.102
When we start preparations
for next season,

00:13:06.223 --> 00:13:10.063
and if we lose two pre-season matches,
the question is asked why it happened.

00:13:10.177 --> 00:13:12.537
If a player isn’t good enough,
he’s replaced immediately.

00:13:12.644 --> 00:13:14.324
That is something incredible.

00:13:14.500 --> 00:13:19.980
Did you become the ultimate
professional at Real?

00:13:20.142 --> 00:13:23.062
Put aside the fact that you always
liked playing football.

00:13:23.249 --> 00:13:27.284
Did playing in that environment
contribute... I'll explain.

00:13:27.369 --> 00:13:33.809
Vidić once said, when leaving
Spartak, also a big club...

00:13:33.978 --> 00:13:40.738
He played for Zvezda, and also in Russia.
Spartak was the biggest club in the USSR.

00:13:41.049 --> 00:13:43.489
He once said the biggest shock
at Manchester United

00:13:43.674 --> 00:13:48.675
was that after training no players
were in the locker room.

00:13:49.306 --> 00:13:52.207
Next day he found himself
in the same situation.

00:13:52.410 --> 00:13:54.659
Because all players behaved
professionally: one getting a massage,

00:13:54.871 --> 00:13:58.121
another in the gym,
Rooney practicing free kicks.

00:13:59.369 --> 00:14:04.137
That’s when he learned that after training
you don’t go to the shower and then home.

00:14:04.274 --> 00:14:08.559
That's how you become
the ultimate professional.

00:14:08.740 --> 00:14:13.895
I know you loved football since childhood,
but did Real teach you that?

00:14:14.096 --> 00:14:17.216
Definitely, I can say it did.

00:14:17.620 --> 00:14:25.540
After the second or third year
at Real, I hired a trainer.

00:14:26.927 --> 00:14:29.514
Probably because the others
also trained with a personal trainer.

00:14:29.653 --> 00:14:32.780
Because everyone else works extra.
You said earlier, none of them

00:14:32.909 --> 00:14:35.975
went straight to the shower
after training and then home.

00:14:36.096 --> 00:14:38.816
Or to lunch, or anywhere else.
They would go to the gym,

00:14:38.977 --> 00:14:43.803
massage, play basketball,
tennis or badminton.

00:14:43.992 --> 00:14:46.832
They were always active.
-They are active. -Yes.

00:14:47.071 --> 00:14:56.153
I always loved training and working,
but at Real I hired a conditioning coach

00:14:56.347 --> 00:15:09.015
to improve my physical ability. To prevent
injuries. -You did it as precaution.

00:15:09.540 --> 00:15:15.980
Real forces you into that.
-Yes, you’re right.

00:15:16.263 --> 00:15:20.543
When you see great players
training, you just can't go home.

00:15:20.871 --> 00:15:23.511
And when players in the
national team see you training,

00:15:23.665 --> 00:15:26.945
they also won’t go sit in the bus.

00:15:27.620 --> 00:15:34.620
Your coaches were Mourinho,
Ancelotti, Benitez, Zidane.

00:15:35.580 --> 00:15:42.420
Did they have anything in common?
Or something that made them unique?

00:15:43.220 --> 00:15:48.300
Each of them is special in his own way.
I don't like to compare people,

00:15:48.460 --> 00:15:52.300
because every coach has
his own way of working.

00:15:52.540 --> 00:15:55.620
Every coach has his own
character, his personality.

00:15:57.860 --> 00:16:01.060
One is very close with
the team, another not.

00:16:01.420 --> 00:16:04.820
Some of them work
much more on tactics.

00:16:05.860 --> 00:16:11.340
Some cooperate more with the players.
It's hard for me to compare them,

00:16:11.478 --> 00:16:15.572
but from each of them...
-You I learned a lot. -A lot.

00:16:15.723 --> 00:16:22.564
Very much. I have a special
feeling towards Mourinho.

00:16:23.220 --> 00:16:26.392
He brought you to Real. -Yes.
And other things I already said.

00:16:26.831 --> 00:16:29.391
He was the person most
responsible for me coming to Real.

00:16:29.585 --> 00:16:32.985
If it weren't for him, maybe it would
never have happened.

00:16:33.217 --> 00:16:37.577
With Carlo, that first spell was incredible.
When we won La Decima,

00:16:37.847 --> 00:16:41.287
the Copa del Rey, and later
when he came back,

00:16:41.542 --> 00:16:45.502
we won two more Champions Leagues.
We also won La Liga twice.

00:16:46.300 --> 00:16:55.220
He’s a very special person. As a man
and as a coach, he is extraordinary.

00:16:55.700 --> 00:17:03.300
Benitez stayed a short time,
but I learned from him too.

00:17:04.180 --> 00:17:08.300
With Zizou, we won three Champions
Leagues in a row. -He is special.

00:17:08.580 --> 00:17:12.140
He is unbelievable. Just his
arrival in the locker room,

00:17:12.380 --> 00:17:17.500
the way he greeted us, for us players
that was something special.

00:17:17.601 --> 00:17:20.231
When we were kids,
we watched him on TV.

00:17:20.294 --> 00:17:22.682
He is one of the best players
in football history,

00:17:22.814 --> 00:17:25.355
and now he was supposed
to be your coach.

00:17:25.546 --> 00:17:29.751
He came, greeted us,
and we started training.

00:17:29.940 --> 00:17:33.462
Regardless of the fact
he was Carlo’s assistant

00:17:33.576 --> 00:17:36.212
when we won the 10th
Champions League title.

00:17:36.295 --> 00:17:39.255
Then he went to coach youth categories
and returned after two years.

00:17:39.425 --> 00:17:45.915
But this time as head coach. As assistant
he was more withdrawn, more reserved.

00:17:46.101 --> 00:17:49.301
But as head coach he was
really phenomenal.

00:17:49.462 --> 00:17:53.622
And we didn’t win three Champions
Leagues in a row by accident.

00:17:53.783 --> 00:17:59.503
He has a special aura.
He knows football well.

00:17:59.825 --> 00:18:05.225
He didn’t try to invent much, he knew
exactly what the team needed.

00:18:05.458 --> 00:18:08.751
Because he had been a player
and knew what must be done.

00:18:08.877 --> 00:18:13.562
He understood the quality
of the players he had.

00:18:14.132 --> 00:18:18.710
He gave us freedom, but there
were things he demanded.

00:18:18.968 --> 00:18:21.928
He rotated the players a lot.
-That's right.

00:18:22.300 --> 00:18:27.377
His philosophy was that every player
is important. And it truly is so.

00:18:27.502 --> 00:18:33.260
He didn't just say that,
he showed it in action.

00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:41.300
Even the one who played the least
still played at least 15 to 20 matches.

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:43.795
Yes, and you have to win
every match. -You’re right.

00:18:43.954 --> 00:18:46.154
That period with him was really special.

00:18:46.354 --> 00:18:58.049
He also played football with us
during training. Small goals.

00:18:58.372 --> 00:19:04.611
It was great. -Yes. Maybe he couldn’t
run much, but his quality was clear.

00:19:04.940 --> 00:19:07.820
His game was like ballet.

00:19:08.140 --> 00:19:16.103
No one has ever played football
like that. -He was a special player.

00:19:16.820 --> 00:19:20.660
Also, he was honest.
And I value that in a coach.

00:19:20.900 --> 00:19:24.808
Mourinho was like that too, he tells
you right away what he thinks.

00:19:24.896 --> 00:19:27.144
He immediately tells you
where you make mistakes.

00:19:27.260 --> 00:19:30.449
He doesn't hesitate to tell
any player where he’s wrong.

00:19:30.566 --> 00:19:34.738
He is direct and straightforward. If he
promises something, it really happens.

00:19:36.243 --> 00:19:40.582
These are giants who are complete.
You know when people say Ancelotti

00:19:40.735 --> 00:19:43.393
doesn't know much about tactics,
that he... That's not true at all.

00:19:43.560 --> 00:19:46.324
That's simply not the case.
Those are stupid things.

00:19:46.451 --> 00:19:49.910
Those are prejudices. -He knows
everything about tactics.

00:19:50.118 --> 00:19:54.160
But he chooses certain things
because he’s the coach in Madrid.

00:19:54.425 --> 00:20:00.160
He knows what kind of players he has,
so he won’t push you too hard.

00:20:00.275 --> 00:20:04.246
He won’t insist on tactics,
he’ll focus on something else.

00:20:04.351 --> 00:20:06.951
These are people who know
everything very well.

00:20:07.068 --> 00:20:09.261
They know absolutely
everything about football.

00:20:09.364 --> 00:20:11.246
Football was invented
long ago. -That's right.

00:20:11.368 --> 00:20:17.246
There is no need to complicate
and try the impossible. -That's right.

00:20:17.758 --> 00:20:23.718
Today everything is getting
more complicated,

00:20:23.919 --> 00:20:29.613
you no longer know what
anyone is saying. -That is correct.

00:20:31.220 --> 00:20:38.300
With every success your familly grows
as well. You have three children.

00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:42.820
You once told me that you all
became so accustomed to Madrid,

00:20:43.020 --> 00:20:46.940
especially the children, that when you
asked them whether you should go home,

00:20:47.140 --> 00:20:50.980
"home" for them meant Madrid.
That is completely natural,

00:20:51.220 --> 00:20:56.660
and it's the same for you. -Yes.
To be honest, it's the same for me.

00:20:56.900 --> 00:20:59.220
Of course, I love Zadar.
I spend my summers there,

00:20:59.420 --> 00:21:03.860
enjoy time with my friends,
we play cards, we go swimming,

00:21:04.100 --> 00:21:11.301
everyday things. But when you say,
"When are we going home?"

00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:15.700
or when they ask, they mean Madrid,
they've lived their entire lives there.

00:21:15.900 --> 00:21:21.106
Ivano was with us in London for 2 years,
but Sofi and Ema have practically

00:21:21.239 --> 00:21:26.067
lived their whole lives in Madrid, as
has Ivano. So for them, home is Madrid,

00:21:26.740 --> 00:21:30.020
their friends, their school,
everything is there.

00:21:30.260 --> 00:21:33.300
And when you look at it,
as we mentioned earlier,

00:21:33.900 --> 00:21:38.940
the longest continuous period you've
spent anywhere hasn't been in Zagreb

00:21:39.180 --> 00:21:44.260
or in Zadar... -I was in Zadars until I
turned 15... -... but really in Madrid.

00:21:44.431 --> 00:21:46.031
Yes, it is Madrid.

00:21:49.300 --> 00:21:52.860
And it's a great city, isn't it?
And when you look at it...

00:21:53.300 --> 00:21:56.500
You mentioned the first time
you walked into the dressing room.

00:21:56.654 --> 00:21:59.623
Is it, in a way, one of Real Madrid's
secrets that constant renewal?

00:21:59.778 --> 00:22:05.389
What I want to ask is: did you miss the
players with whom you won everything?

00:22:06.300 --> 00:22:12.460
The other day, I put this down on paper
when I was thinking about all this...

00:22:12.740 --> 00:22:20.140
Casillas left, Pepe left, then Arbeloa
left, then Ramos, later Marcelo,

00:22:20.500 --> 00:22:27.780
then Ronaldo, Bale, Kroos,
and Higuaín, right? -Yes, yes.

00:22:28.380 --> 00:22:35.760
But then new players arrive, and not
just anyone, the very best come in...

00:22:35.994 --> 00:22:39.456
Those are exceptional players.
-Did you miss the old ones a lot?

00:22:39.740 --> 00:22:43.809
Yes, especially some with whom
I built an incredible relationship,

00:22:43.930 --> 00:22:46.650
which I still have today,
both family-wise and as close friends.

00:22:46.853 --> 00:22:53.933
When Marcelo left, I missed him a lot.
Sergio, Mateo... -Mateo. -Mateo.

00:22:54.164 --> 00:22:56.723
Well, yes, but Mateo
also wanted to leave.

00:22:56.810 --> 00:22:59.707
And generally, at Real,
they push you out, right?

00:22:59.826 --> 00:23:02.832
Yes, at Real, they do push you out.
-Like you said earlier about Rodrygo...

00:23:02.903 --> 00:23:06.103
You don't leave unless they push you
out. -And Mateo wanted to play.

00:23:06.194 --> 00:23:08.957
He wanted to play, even though,
in my opinion, he played a lot.

00:23:09.064 --> 00:23:13.354
In that period at Real, he was,
in my view, one of the best players,

00:23:13.494 --> 00:23:16.307
although he may disagree. Even
if he wasn't the main protagonist

00:23:16.459 --> 00:23:19.338
the whole time, he played outstanding
matches and was very important.

00:23:19.473 --> 00:23:21.900
He wanted to be the protagonist,
to be on the pitch constantly,

00:23:22.080 --> 00:23:26.816
the way Toni, Casemiro and I were,
but he still played phenomenal football.

00:23:28.820 --> 00:23:34.900
It was hard for me when he left because
Mateo is someone truly special to me.

00:23:35.700 --> 00:23:39.580
From the very beginning, from the moment
he came to the national team,

00:23:39.780 --> 00:23:45.580
we created an exceptional relationship,
a chemistry that lasts to this day,

00:23:45.860 --> 00:23:51.420
even after he left Real.
At Real, we became even closer,

00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:59.620
but often when someone leaves,
paths naturally separate.

00:23:59.820 --> 00:24:05.900
With him, it became even stronger.
Even stronger, actually.

00:24:07.380 --> 00:24:12.460
So it's not just a friendship,
but also a bond through family ties,

00:24:12.660 --> 00:24:16.660
and because of that, you miss all those
players who left at certain moments.

00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:21.700
But that's simply how it is,
and you get used to it.

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:28.540
I'm thinking now,
is there that dual positive effect?

00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:34.820
On one hand, new world-class players
arrive, after all it's Real Madrid,

00:24:35.060 --> 00:24:40.020
and their arrival brings new motivation
and a fresh impulse to the team.

00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:46.060
On the other hand, no matter how much
you've won as a Real Madrid player,

00:24:46.340 --> 00:24:49.900
the fact that the club regularly moves
players on creates additional pressure:

00:24:50.140 --> 00:24:55.220
you have to be at your best
at all times if you want to stay.

00:24:55.460 --> 00:25:00.060
There is no moment of easing off,
no sense of "I'll slow down a little."

00:25:00.260 --> 00:25:05.500
There's none of that in Real.
They simply do not tolerate mediocrity.

00:25:05.623 --> 00:25:08.343
If they sense that you are
even slightly below your level,

00:25:08.480 --> 00:25:10.966
they immediately start
looking for other solutions.

00:25:11.091 --> 00:25:13.771
The competition is enormous,
and you really have to be at the top.

00:25:14.100 --> 00:25:17.820
Because someone behind you is waiting
for you to play one bad match

00:25:18.020 --> 00:25:22.060
so he can step in. But in a healthy way.
-Yes, yes, of course.

00:25:22.580 --> 00:25:30.199
It's a daily pressure, a constant
expectation that you need to be

00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:35.760
at the top, because if you're not,
others will come.

00:25:35.990 --> 00:25:40.220
That's simply the nature of the job.
I managed to stay for long time.

00:25:40.420 --> 00:25:46.327
From that perspective
happy and proud that,

00:25:46.835 --> 00:25:56.780
I am highly competitive. Whoever arrives,
especially when younger players come in,

00:25:57.060 --> 00:26:02.260
the talk has been that the older ones
should slowly be moved aside.

00:26:02.540 --> 00:26:07.460
That has been said since
the World Cup in Russia.

00:26:07.820 --> 00:26:11.260
That actually gave me extra motivation
to show that I can still keep up

00:26:11.389 --> 00:26:14.829
with the younger players
and that I am still 'that guy'.

00:26:15.047 --> 00:26:19.647
That competition motivated me
and kept me at this level.

00:26:20.020 --> 00:26:23.460
Your role on the pitch is,

00:26:26.660 --> 00:26:31.186
objectively speaking, extraordinary.
What you do on the pitch...

00:26:31.400 --> 00:26:35.413
Actually, this is where
I wanted to ask you something.

00:26:36.660 --> 00:26:39.687
You are a creator, an artist,
a genius, but at the same time,

00:26:39.808 --> 00:26:42.859
you are also the player
who does all the "other" work.

00:26:43.091 --> 00:26:48.789
How do you enter that special zone?
Of course, you prepare for a match

00:26:48.973 --> 00:26:53.812
and analyze other professionals.
Do you enter some kind of trance?

00:26:53.993 --> 00:26:56.656
Some kind of madness.
You can't go into "madness,"

00:26:56.791 --> 00:27:02.898
that's for Vinicius or some other forward
who can disappear for 80 minutes

00:27:03.033 --> 00:27:05.710
and then appear for 10 minutes,
and you are not that type.

00:27:05.884 --> 00:27:10.679
You can win a match with a goal,
very often with an assist,

00:27:10.841 --> 00:27:17.841
but your role is much bigger.
You control the tempo, the rhythm,

00:27:18.010 --> 00:27:23.804
the pulse of the match. You decide
where and how the game will be played

00:27:24.515 --> 00:27:27.700
for all 90 minutes, without a pause...

00:27:27.940 --> 00:27:33.460
And you've been doing it
every three days for 20 years.

00:27:34.300 --> 00:27:37.618
And we're talking about Real,
where, as you just said,

00:27:37.806 --> 00:27:42.766
there is no credit, and where everyone
expects everything from you:

00:27:42.973 --> 00:27:47.733
your teammates, the coach,
the management, the media, the fans,

00:27:47.886 --> 00:27:54.446
and ultimately you yourself.
How do you enter that state?

00:27:55.780 --> 00:27:59.660
It's simply a state
that is hard to explain...

00:28:00.180 --> 00:28:06.060
Everything around you seems not to
exist-only the pitch, the ball,

00:28:06.260 --> 00:28:10.660
your teammates, and you are
entirely focused on that.

00:28:11.140 --> 00:28:17.753
No distraction can pull you out of it.
That is where I feel most comfortable.

00:28:17.862 --> 00:28:21.386
When you have problems, you come onto
the pitch, and you forget everything.

00:28:21.540 --> 00:28:24.780
You feel most comfortable on the pitch?
-Yes. You forget everything.

00:28:25.060 --> 00:28:30.060
If you have a problem, God forbid,
you come onto the pitch,

00:28:30.260 --> 00:28:34.700
and for those 90 minutes or more,
nothing else exists.

00:28:34.940 --> 00:28:39.930
Only the ball, the pitch, the players...
-Do you know what Maradona said?

00:28:40.074 --> 00:28:42.214
Sorry to interrupt.
Do you know what he said?

00:28:42.332 --> 00:28:49.126
Maradona said the only time he rests is
during the match. He rests.

00:28:50.140 --> 00:28:54.949
Everything else is exhaustion.
-Yes, yes. That's why I say,

00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:59.750
when you are on the pitch,
nothing else exists.

00:28:59.980 --> 00:29:03.860
You are aware that
expectations are enormous,

00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:06.780
and you know you must remain calm.

00:29:06.980 --> 00:29:10.900
As a midfielder, you cannot
wait for your 10 minutes,

00:29:11.140 --> 00:29:14.740
you have to be at the highest
level the entire time,

00:29:14.980 --> 00:29:21.060
maintain the team's balance, organize
it, show that they can rely on you,

00:29:21.300 --> 00:29:25.460
that you are calm, composed, that
you give support to your teammates,

00:29:25.900 --> 00:29:33.900
guide them, and advise them.
That is my role on the pitch.

00:29:35.020 --> 00:29:43.820
Goals and, let's say, the headline roles
belong to Ronaldo and Benzema

00:29:44.020 --> 00:29:50.220
more than to midfielders. But without
the midfield, a team can hardly perform,

00:29:50.420 --> 00:29:54.940
it cannot maintain balance or quality.

00:29:55.180 --> 00:29:59.380
There's a reason why people say the
midfield always decides everything.

00:29:59.478 --> 00:30:02.133
The only sport where the center
is the most crucial part.

00:30:02.226 --> 00:30:04.595
It is the most important,
that's right. You have to be...

00:30:04.766 --> 00:30:09.646
When you walk out for a match, and
this has been going on for years now,

00:30:09.847 --> 00:30:14.051
where do you see your advantage? Where
do you spot that you are the player,

00:30:14.137 --> 00:30:17.308
that you have something
your opponent does not have?

00:30:18.872 --> 00:30:24.371
I don't know, that's... -Where do you
feel that strength during the match?

00:30:26.540 --> 00:30:32.420
I think it's in recognizing situations
on the pitch. -That's it, exactly.

00:30:32.740 --> 00:30:39.300
Yes. That's where I make the difference,
because sometimes I see things

00:30:39.900 --> 00:30:45.300
before they actually happen.
So I think that is, let's say,

00:30:46.820 --> 00:30:52.820
a difference compared to others,
but it is difficult to talk about myself.

00:30:53.060 --> 00:30:56.180
But that's exactly it...
-And I don't like talking about myself.

00:30:56.380 --> 00:31:00.900
I believe my character is
also fundamental there.

00:31:01.140 --> 00:31:04.820
I am a fighter, I never give up,
I never see defeat as final.

00:31:05.380 --> 00:31:12.620
Even when a situation seems hopeless,
I always think that a solution

00:31:12.860 --> 00:31:17.620
can be found, that something
can be done, that things can improve.

00:31:17.790 --> 00:31:20.630
I will never say it is over,
that there is no way out,

00:31:20.829 --> 00:31:23.269
there is always something
that can be done.

00:31:23.486 --> 00:31:26.806
So that character, and that mindset...
-Well, that's it.

00:31:27.282 --> 00:31:30.922
That is precisely it, that is character
and everything that comes with it,

00:31:31.380 --> 00:31:33.660
your anticipation,
understanding of the game,

00:31:33.900 --> 00:31:37.300
reading of the game in both phases,
even more so in the defensive phase,

00:31:37.540 --> 00:31:44.700
when you almost know where the ball
will drop. Like Rodman or Barkley,

00:31:44.940 --> 00:31:48.300
they weren't the tallest, yet they had
the most rebounds because they knew

00:31:48.540 --> 00:31:52.140
where the ball would land.
And you are like that...

00:31:52.340 --> 00:31:57.060
This has followed you from the
beginning, that "What is he exactly?",

00:31:57.189 --> 00:31:59.949
but in a positive sense, even back
when you were in the youth setup.

00:32:00.133 --> 00:32:05.613
If you're a number 10,
then it's a shame you're not deeper,

00:32:05.940 --> 00:32:10.367
a shame you're not lower on the pitch
because you're so good on the ball.

00:32:11.060 --> 00:32:14.660
If you play deeper, then it's a shame
you're not closer to the goal

00:32:14.860 --> 00:32:19.180
for that final pass or the finish.

00:32:19.740 --> 00:32:23.460
I think it was Bielsa who said,

00:32:23.660 --> 00:32:28.580
"Is he a 6, an 8, or a 10? He's
a 24-he's all of that in one". -Yes.

00:32:32.060 --> 00:32:35.220
You were always, in a way,

00:32:37.972 --> 00:32:40.012
ahead of your time.

00:32:42.140 --> 00:32:47.460
But what is also very interesting
and should be underlined is

00:32:47.780 --> 00:32:51.700
how your role at Real has grown.

00:32:52.140 --> 00:32:56.500
You arrived at Real Madrid,
already then the best-known,

00:32:56.740 --> 00:33:01.620
biggest club in the world, to strengthen
the quality and competition

00:33:01.900 --> 00:33:07.460
in midfield in 2012, right? -Yes.
-Xabi Alonso, Khedira, and Özil

00:33:07.700 --> 00:33:11.460
were already there. And then
another player arrives - you.

00:33:11.820 --> 00:33:18.340
From that point, you become
a starter, a protagonist,

00:33:19.140 --> 00:33:26.100
the director and main creator,
a captain, a mentor, everything.

00:33:26.246 --> 00:33:28.646
None of that was handed to you,

00:33:28.784 --> 00:33:34.711
you had to build it all step by step
over these thirteen years.

00:33:36.962 --> 00:33:40.303
Let's say everything unfolded
in its own natural way.

00:33:40.398 --> 00:33:44.223
There were highs and lows, of course.
-Turbulences, naturally.

00:33:44.337 --> 00:33:47.411
But I think everything went
the way it was meant to go.

00:33:47.545 --> 00:33:54.705
I believe I would choose the same path
again, I wouldn't change anything.

00:33:55.131 --> 00:33:59.811
So, I guess it all progressed
exactly as it should have, step by step,

00:34:00.300 --> 00:34:03.380
without skipping any stages.

00:34:05.500 --> 00:34:12.380
Regarding my positions on the pitch,
I think it helped me a lot

00:34:12.900 --> 00:34:17.420
that throughout my career, in the
youth categories and later at Zrinjski

00:34:17.620 --> 00:34:21.260
and Inter, I played in
several different roles.

00:34:21.540 --> 00:34:24.220
I wasn't just a central or
right midfielder, for example,

00:34:24.460 --> 00:34:32.180
I played as a second striker
and left winger in a 4-4-2 or 4-3-3.

00:34:32.420 --> 00:34:36.460
And as a winger... -... and in a 4-4-2
as one of two midfielders,

00:34:36.700 --> 00:34:39.740
and I even played right wing
for Zrinjski at the beginning.

00:34:40.260 --> 00:34:44.780
So I played as a second striker,
and I switched positions constantly.

00:34:45.420 --> 00:34:48.740
The first ones who put me in
the defensive midfield role

00:34:48.940 --> 00:34:53.220
were you and Harry Redknapp. -Yes.
-Into that central position. -Yes, yes.

00:34:53.500 --> 00:34:57.900
Which in England was a big surprise.
-It takes a sort of a "palacio"...

00:34:58.543 --> 00:35:05.263
So that helped me a lot in becoming good
defensively and in reading the game.

00:35:05.540 --> 00:35:10.340
All that mixing of positions,
I think, helped enormously.

00:35:10.540 --> 00:35:14.060
That is your special quality on
the pitch. I was at those matches.

00:35:14.340 --> 00:35:18.820
I was at those matches,
I saw them up close,

00:35:19.660 --> 00:35:25.940
and that's why I never understood
where those debates come from.

00:35:26.220 --> 00:35:32.580
In that exact match Real against
Chelsea, when you won in London,

00:35:32.900 --> 00:35:36.540
and when Benzema scored
a hat-trick... -... 3-1.

00:35:36.677 --> 00:35:39.557
... and then took matters
into his own hands in Madrid...

00:35:39.742 --> 00:35:43.542
That match was the one where you gave
Rodrygo that incredible assist

00:35:43.719 --> 00:35:50.759
with the outside of your right foot,
one of the best you've ever produced.

00:35:51.117 --> 00:35:56.157
And it's not just me saying that, Rio
Ferdinand and half the world said that.

00:35:56.473 --> 00:36:00.713
However, in that match, what I was
seeing was something else entirely:

00:36:00.857 --> 00:36:04.758
the way you marked Rüdiger
on set pieces, at corners,

00:36:04.881 --> 00:36:08.923
back when he was still
a Chelsea player.

00:36:09.103 --> 00:36:14.899
You didn't do it asking yourself,
"Why am I marking Rüdiger?"

00:36:15.024 --> 00:36:18.691
Even though he's taller
and physically stronger,

00:36:18.875 --> 00:36:21.716
you marked him exactly
the way he needed to be marked.

00:36:22.020 --> 00:36:25.220
You made his game difficult,
and you were precise in every duel.

00:36:25.460 --> 00:36:29.380
And in the same match,
after taking a corner,

00:36:29.580 --> 00:36:33.820
you were the furthest player forward,
and you stopped their counterattack.

00:36:34.020 --> 00:36:41.540
That shows your completeness. And that's
why it surprises me when someone asks,

00:36:42.380 --> 00:36:45.500
"Is he this or that?"
Because the truth is very simple,

00:36:45.700 --> 00:36:50.300
you are all of it at once.
You are everything.

00:36:52.260 --> 00:37:00.140
Yes... And from a young age, I learned
responsibility in life in general,

00:37:00.660 --> 00:37:05.540
which naturally translated onto
the pitch. I left Zadar on my own,

00:37:05.780 --> 00:37:09.620
I had to manage everything myself,
make my own breakfast, figure out

00:37:09.820 --> 00:37:15.820
lunch and dinner... and that
responsibility I carried off the pitch,

00:37:16.100 --> 00:37:21.260
that is exactly how I am on the pitch
as well. -And that is the whole story,

00:37:21.500 --> 00:37:23.940
that's exactly what we've been
talking about here.

00:37:24.180 --> 00:37:27.500
You had one pair of Ronaldo's shin
guards, and instinctively you knew...

00:37:27.700 --> 00:37:30.700
You had one pair, and three days later,
you didn't show up asking for a pair

00:37:30.940 --> 00:37:34.060
from Rooney, then one from Beckham,
then losing a pair and saying,

00:37:34.300 --> 00:37:37.420
"It doesn't matter, Stipe will
get me new ones from Boban..."

00:37:37.660 --> 00:37:40.580
You know, if you don't
throw away a slice of bread,

00:37:40.820 --> 00:37:44.860
and if your shin guards matter, then
every ball in a match also matters.

00:37:45.060 --> 00:37:47.420
I've said this a hundred times.

00:37:47.660 --> 00:37:53.700
I coached you, and I saw how you reacted
in training, which I never told you,

00:37:53.940 --> 00:38:00.980
but I've said it to a 1000 other people,
when you lost the ball in training,

00:38:01.260 --> 00:38:04.860
and by your standard, which is extremely
high, you shouldn't have lost it,

00:38:05.100 --> 00:38:11.220
you went mad. And I'm talking
about training, not a match.

00:38:11.420 --> 00:38:14.820
What level of responsibility is that...
-And it's still like that today.

00:38:15.020 --> 00:38:20.300
Even today... And when someone
makes a mistake, and the cameras

00:38:20.540 --> 00:38:25.180
catch your reaction, you get upset.
What's wrong? -Yes, yes. -That's it.

00:38:25.380 --> 00:38:31.380
I can be a perfectionist at times,
but of course, you can't be perfect,

00:38:31.540 --> 00:38:34.860
though I try... -You should strive for it.
-Yes, you should strive for it.

00:38:35.100 --> 00:38:38.905
Luka, you're speaking brilliantly.
This is fantastic.

00:38:39.140 --> 00:38:43.540
Truly phenomenal reflections.
Now, Real aside for a moment...

00:38:43.740 --> 00:38:46.820
Let's go to the national team.
We touched on 2006, 2008,

00:38:47.020 --> 00:38:53.060
2010, unfortunately, we weren't there,
then 2012, and before Russia,

00:38:53.300 --> 00:38:58.780
there were the 2014 World Cup in Brazil
and the 2016 Euro in France.

00:39:02.700 --> 00:39:07.660
In Brazil, that... How did you
see those two tournaments?

00:39:07.900 --> 00:39:11.220
The World Cup in Brazil
and the Euro in France...

00:39:11.420 --> 00:39:14.700
Well, the World Cup in Brazil...

00:39:16.220 --> 00:39:21.980
Let's say this without
calling anyone out now:

00:39:22.220 --> 00:39:29.180
it was our worst tournament and
the worst atmosphere the national team

00:39:29.380 --> 00:39:34.340
has ever seen. From the beginning,
you could feel we had no chance

00:39:34.540 --> 00:39:40.260
of achieving anything,
no progress, you could sense it.

00:39:40.500 --> 00:39:45.900
I was there, it was after
the end of the season with Real.

00:39:46.044 --> 00:39:49.241
I came in extremely exhausted,
it had been a long season,

00:39:49.692 --> 00:39:53.612
and I played practically without rest.
My worst tournament, without...

00:39:53.867 --> 00:39:58.197
I've never liked hiding behind excuses,
and I said the same thing back then,

00:39:58.416 --> 00:40:01.980
after the tournament. But the
environment and atmosphere in the team

00:40:02.260 --> 00:40:08.900
had never been worse. There were,
let's say, specific groups.

00:40:09.140 --> 00:40:13.940
Which is strange for the national team,
because usually it's balanced, united...

00:40:14.180 --> 00:40:18.260
We always talk about and pride ourselves
on that atmosphere, that environment,

00:40:18.500 --> 00:40:22.380
that unity which gives us strength
and which carried us to our

00:40:22.620 --> 00:40:26.260
biggest successes, because without that,
there is no chance, you can forget it.

00:40:26.500 --> 00:40:31.260
You can have quality, but without unity,
you can forget about achieving results.

00:40:31.820 --> 00:40:34.220
But in that tournament, we simply...

00:40:34.540 --> 00:40:37.996
We weren't a group,
we didn't have togetherness,

00:40:38.496 --> 00:40:45.620
and we finished the way we finished.
At the next Euro in France,

00:40:46.100 --> 00:40:52.508
we played excellent football,
and the atmosphere was much better.

00:40:52.820 --> 00:40:59.008
That sense of unity returned,
but even then, among us players...

00:40:59.336 --> 00:41:03.740
We still weren't entirely on ideal terms.

00:41:03.980 --> 00:41:08.100
We somehow managed to fix it
and put ourselves at the service

00:41:08.580 --> 00:41:12.580
of the national team,
trying to get the best result.

00:41:13.100 --> 00:41:16.980
We were very close. We missed
by little against Portugal.

00:41:17.220 --> 00:41:20.020
We played well. Against Turkey
we played excellent,

00:41:20.220 --> 00:41:26.140
we beat Spain. Against the Czechs
we played fantastic 60 minutes,

00:41:26.380 --> 00:41:30.500
until that interruption. -Yes, yes.
-Then Portugal came.

00:41:30.700 --> 00:41:36.460
We had chances and
good situations to win.

00:41:37.140 --> 00:41:41.660
Probably it wasn’t the time
or it wasn’t meant to be.

00:41:41.860 --> 00:41:47.660
We went out to the future champs.
Had we won, the draw ahead

00:41:47.860 --> 00:41:52.980
would have opened for us
to go all the way, like 2012.

00:41:53.220 --> 00:41:56.300
Had we passed the group,
we’d have gone all the way. Sure.

00:41:56.580 --> 00:41:59.300
But... -But we showed
very good football.

00:41:59.500 --> 00:42:07.020
Quite painful... Not like 2008 shock,
but again last minute...

00:42:07.260 --> 00:42:11.100
You think maybe penalties.
But better to go out like that

00:42:11.340 --> 00:42:17.060
than reach penalties and lose. -Yes.
-But that’s the usual "what if".

00:42:17.540 --> 00:42:22.300
It was a big shock.
I even cried on the pitch.

00:42:22.500 --> 00:42:26.780
Didn’t think I’d... -Show that.
-... show that on the pitch.

00:42:27.260 --> 00:42:32.340
I opened there and emotions
came out because of the loss.

00:42:32.540 --> 00:42:41.700
You think 2008, 2012, always close,
but there's no breakthrough.

00:42:41.940 --> 00:42:46.500
You wonder how much time is left.
-Yes, yes. -When will we do it?

00:42:46.700 --> 00:42:54.300
We were burdened by your
generation. We were always told:

00:42:54.389 --> 00:42:59.143
"Bronze, bronze, bronze."
You inspired us. -Yes.

00:42:59.347 --> 00:43:02.401
We looked up to idols growing up.
-Later it became a burden.

00:43:02.542 --> 00:43:07.698
Later it became heavy,
because it was always there.

00:43:07.956 --> 00:43:12.380
You say "leave us alone".
We’re a new generation,

00:43:12.660 --> 00:43:18.860
making our path. We’ll see
what we do, don’t pressure us.

00:43:19.060 --> 00:43:23.820
They were special. Our idols.
Inspiration... -But you already

00:43:24.020 --> 00:43:27.540
play in top clubs. -We play...
You play in better clubs than us.

00:43:27.740 --> 00:43:32.940
Yes, but we weren’t mature yet.
-Like in 1996 we weren’t...

00:43:33.180 --> 00:43:38.980
Possible. To achieve something big.
But it came, thank God, two years later.

00:43:39.180 --> 00:43:45.100
You, even in 2008, when you
were young, as we said earlier,

00:43:45.340 --> 00:43:51.820
took a third-minute penalty
against hosts Austria.

00:43:52.180 --> 00:43:55.660
You’re a leader on the pitch,
but you’re not loud.

00:43:56.260 --> 00:44:01.180
Later when Niko Kovač retired
and I wanted you to take number 10,

00:44:01.420 --> 00:44:07.020
at first... didn’t want it...
You were always a leader

00:44:07.260 --> 00:44:16.002
on the pitch, but not loud off it.
Fun, part of the group.

00:44:16.204 --> 00:44:18.084
In the group you’re a leader. Of course.

00:44:19.140 --> 00:44:22.940
But you don’t insist on others,
except on the pitch. -Yes.

00:44:23.340 --> 00:44:28.740
So after Euro 2016,
Darijo Srna was a top captain.

00:44:28.980 --> 00:44:33.340
You helped him, and you were
among the captains too. -Yes.

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:42.260
You were great. Darijo leaves and
you become the captain. Russia game.

00:44:43.180 --> 00:44:51.780
And you... as the book says, I didn’t
know this either. You decide to take

00:44:52.020 --> 00:44:55.441
some things into your own hands,
like conflicts, though it sounds silly,

00:44:55.637 --> 00:44:59.917
with Mandžo, and other non-football
matters. Tell us about that. -Yes.

00:45:01.980 --> 00:45:10.180
They labelled me. They threw at me
"he’s small, skinny, won’t make it".

00:45:10.420 --> 00:45:16.660
On the other hand, when I reached
certain levels, "not a leader,

00:45:17.140 --> 00:45:24.340
he lacks this, he’s not the one."
But I have that inside me.

00:45:24.580 --> 00:45:27.300
At some point you think
you shouldn’t show it,

00:45:27.540 --> 00:45:29.780
because you don’t want
to break the hierarchy.

00:45:30.020 --> 00:45:34.540
You know who the captain is.
Hierarchy must be respected.

00:45:34.820 --> 00:45:38.900
But when something
had to be said, I said it.

00:45:39.340 --> 00:45:47.860
I prefer and look up more
to leaders by example, not words,

00:45:48.140 --> 00:45:52.620
so you do things that sometimes
go against my views and rules

00:45:52.900 --> 00:46:03.457
that I have in my head. I always
tried to be that kind of leader.

00:46:06.620 --> 00:46:15.020
When I became captain...
I spoke about 2014, then 2016,

00:46:15.260 --> 00:46:22.540
which was better, but with some
players I’d been through a lot

00:46:22.820 --> 00:46:27.860
and had small disagreements.
Whether because of me or them,

00:46:28.060 --> 00:46:33.500
or some statements. As the feeling
grew that this might be our last

00:46:33.700 --> 00:46:38.192
World Cup, a chance for the
generation to do something big,

00:46:38.707 --> 00:46:44.968
players were in big clubs.
They were not just numbers there,

00:46:45.133 --> 00:46:49.811
but protagonists, very important
players of those big clubs.

00:46:49.930 --> 00:46:56.554
Juventus, Milan, Real, Barça...
-Inter. -Inter, Monaco... -Liverpool.

00:46:56.734 --> 00:47:06.294
Liverpool. Incredible. With Mandžo
I hadn’t spoken for years.

00:47:06.660 --> 00:47:13.180
I had, but not like before.
Then, at my insistence,

00:47:13.500 --> 00:47:17.020
before preparations and games
against Liverpool, Senegal,

00:47:17.260 --> 00:47:20.540
I think we were in Opatija,
if I’m not wrong,

00:47:20.820 --> 00:47:24.300
I talked to him. I resolved our issue.

00:47:24.540 --> 00:47:28.900
In the end it was something
really trivial, but... -Doesn’t matter.

00:47:29.620 --> 00:47:33.700
I let it run its course,
he did the same.

00:47:33.940 --> 00:47:38.500
Then it became something
that seemed unsolvable.

00:47:38.700 --> 00:47:43.452
When we finally sat and talked,
it was a small thing. We fixed it.

00:47:43.897 --> 00:47:50.488
I was relieved, probably him too.
The second case was with Čarli,

00:47:51.020 --> 00:47:55.420
because of some statements
that didn’t suit me.

00:47:55.620 --> 00:47:59.460
We didn’t discuss it deeply.
A bit by phone,

00:47:59.700 --> 00:48:03.060
but I don’t like discussing
some things by phone.

00:48:03.300 --> 00:48:07.940
I prefer face to face,
1 on 1, to clarify the issue.

00:48:08.140 --> 00:48:15.860
We fixed that too. I freed myself
from those burdens I had inside.

00:48:16.140 --> 00:48:20.189
I went to that World Cup
with a clear mind.

00:48:21.682 --> 00:48:26.602
I had a feeling, Vanja can
confirm what I told her,

00:48:27.140 --> 00:48:30.460
that we’d do great things
at that World Cup.

00:48:30.660 --> 00:48:37.020
I told her on Ivano’s birthday,
before our match with Brazil

00:48:37.260 --> 00:48:44.380
and before the World Cup. -Yes.
A very important thing was

00:48:45.340 --> 00:48:53.100
Zlatko Dalić arriving. He did and
still does phenomenal things. -Yes.

00:48:53.820 --> 00:49:00.860
When did you feel that special
something? What did he bring?

00:49:01.100 --> 00:49:05.300
When did you feel it... You told
Vanja, right? Before preparations?

00:49:05.540 --> 00:49:08.420
Before World Cup camp.
-You feel something’s coming. -Yes.

00:49:08.620 --> 00:49:12.060
Was that before or after your talks
with Čarli and Mandžukić?

00:49:12.300 --> 00:49:17.340
But you decided you’d talk.
-No, with Vanja, after.

00:49:17.580 --> 00:49:22.620
Before the Senegal match in Osijek...
-Then you got two days off.

00:49:22.860 --> 00:49:27.620
I flew... my son Ivano had
a birthday, I went there.

00:49:27.820 --> 00:49:32.940
Next day we stayed, I had to
return, and we played Liverpool.

00:49:33.140 --> 00:49:35.500
And Brazil. -Yes.

00:49:38.740 --> 00:49:43.900
What were we saying? -That’s when
you felt it... and Zlatko arrived.

00:49:44.053 --> 00:49:47.333
Zlatko arrived practically
at the airport, a day before

00:49:47.501 --> 00:49:50.005
the match vs Ukraine where
only a win was acceptable.

00:49:50.150 --> 00:49:53.599
Exactly. -I didn’t know him.
I knew he coached Rijeka,

00:49:53.750 --> 00:49:57.070
Varaždin and those clubs.
He was abroad too.

00:49:57.942 --> 00:50:04.685
But our first talk, I felt some
incredibly good energy.

00:50:05.585 --> 00:50:11.225
His calmness... -His composure.
-Composure. We were all stressed.

00:50:11.487 --> 00:50:17.686
Maybe we wouldn’t qualify, which
would be tragic for such a generation

00:50:18.186 --> 00:50:25.069
and such players. He brought
calm and good energy.

00:50:25.500 --> 00:50:33.180
He asked for opinions on how
we should play, he said his ideas.

00:50:35.100 --> 00:50:40.660
It was a pleasant talk... -Cooperation.
-Phenomenal cooperation from day one.

00:50:40.845 --> 00:50:44.205
Against Ukraine we
played a great match.

00:50:44.374 --> 00:50:47.694
We needed to win just to
play play-offs. -Da.

00:50:47.872 --> 00:50:53.272
Against... -Greece. -Greece. Of course,
we smashed Greece completely.

00:50:53.411 --> 00:50:57.011
Especially in Zagreb, away game
was a draw. There we...

00:50:59.940 --> 00:51:08.580
A good group started forming,
but then came the US camp.

00:51:09.860 --> 00:51:18.940
We lost to Peru then. That’s when
Čarli’s statement happened.

00:51:19.133 --> 00:51:22.573
Some of us went back to clubs,
we didn’t play vs Mexico.

00:51:24.220 --> 00:51:28.940
He said what he said.
He shouldn’t have, he knows it.

00:51:29.140 --> 00:51:33.820
It passed, everything
was smoothed out.

00:51:35.580 --> 00:51:43.660
Again stories started that this
isn’t the team, this isn’t...

00:51:44.060 --> 00:51:50.900
Doubts. But I’m not someone
for big announcements.

00:51:51.100 --> 00:51:58.740
"We’ll do this, that." I simply
felt we’d do good things.

00:51:58.980 --> 00:52:04.180
I told Vanja before going back
to the national team.

00:52:04.420 --> 00:52:09.540
We talked how, what, because
she didn’t go to the first games.

00:52:09.729 --> 00:52:14.009
She thought we’d fall out
in the group. Not because

00:52:14.217 --> 00:52:20.257
she didn’t believe. She likes
to provoke to give motivation.

00:52:20.712 --> 00:52:28.212
I told her we’ll play a great
tournament, do something big.

00:52:28.342 --> 00:52:32.330
I’ll be the best. -Come on.
-Ask her, you’ll hear.

00:52:32.542 --> 00:52:36.533
That’s how it was. I never say
I’ll be this or that. Never.

00:52:36.655 --> 00:52:44.361
But I said it then, before I left.
In the end we did great things.

00:52:44.548 --> 00:52:50.500
I was player of the tournament.
I had a good feeling.

00:52:52.980 --> 00:52:59.340
We said already. A career lasts
as long as it lasts.

00:52:59.580 --> 00:53:02.700
We know what the national team
means to you, how special

00:53:02.940 --> 00:53:06.660
you feel every time you play.
Each time feels like the first

00:53:06.940 --> 00:53:13.300
and it "charges" you to keep playing
at that level in your club. -Yes.

00:53:14.260 --> 00:53:17.860
But an important moment
of your national team career

00:53:18.060 --> 00:53:25.237
is the penalty vs Denmark.
That’s... exactly, blow, blow.

00:53:25.687 --> 00:53:29.727
Impossible. Everything was
in that one moment.

00:53:30.100 --> 00:53:34.475
Like that series with Ivanišević
in the Wimbledon final.

00:53:34.911 --> 00:53:41.269
You miss a penalty in stoppage...
-118th minute. -... that would pass you.

00:53:41.521 --> 00:53:46.001
Sure. -Or Turkey again.
-Not for sure, we learned something.

00:53:47.070 --> 00:53:51.990
And again penalties. You don’t
feel like doing it, but you must.

00:53:52.820 --> 00:53:58.860
You must as team leader.
If you refuse, you’re already down.

00:53:59.220 --> 00:54:04.420
The team loses confidence.
-Yes. -But I think that...

00:54:04.620 --> 00:54:11.260
That match, that penalty,
shows my character.

00:54:11.540 --> 00:54:14.500
It describes my character when
someone asks what I’m like,

00:54:14.700 --> 00:54:21.020
what my strongest traits are...
-Yes. -I think that match

00:54:21.260 --> 00:54:26.700
describes enough my character.
Of course, that miss...

00:54:26.940 --> 00:54:31.940
I was furious I missed.
I had a good feeling.

00:54:32.180 --> 00:54:38.740
I simply missed, but stayed calm
however much it burned in me.

00:54:38.980 --> 00:54:44.460
It wasn’t like vs Turkey when we
scored in 119th minute

00:54:44.700 --> 00:54:47.860
and already saw ourselves
in the quarterfinal.

00:54:48.060 --> 00:54:52.580
They equalise and then penalties.
We were totally unfocused.

00:54:52.724 --> 00:54:57.051
As if we had already lost, even
though you still have penalties.

00:54:57.732 --> 00:55:03.500
We were younger, totally unfocused.
That’s why we missed three penalties.

00:55:03.740 --> 00:55:08.260
In this situation I stayed calm
and knew I wanted to do it.

00:55:08.500 --> 00:55:13.900
And you’re 10 years older. -Older,
of course. -Raketa, you, the others.

00:55:15.140 --> 00:55:19.260
I wanted to take responsibility,
I wanted to take the penalty.

00:55:19.500 --> 00:55:29.261
I know it would be different if I didn’t.
A big handicap going forward.

00:55:29.862 --> 00:55:33.808
For a captain to step away
when it’s hardest...

00:55:34.113 --> 00:55:37.932
It wasn’t about my career,
but that penalty...

00:55:38.258 --> 00:55:42.698
It defined a lot. -I’d be like
Roberto Baggio.

00:55:42.929 --> 00:55:46.609
He’s always reminded of ’94.
I’d be marked by that penalty.

00:55:46.865 --> 00:55:50.545
Already at that time I wasn’t
rated highly in Croatia

00:55:50.831 --> 00:55:56.991
because of things outside football.
That penalty was... -Everything.

00:55:57.113 --> 00:55:59.193
Everything was in that moment.

00:55:59.384 --> 00:56:04.984
Maybe one of the most important moments
in my national team career. -For sure.

00:56:05.233 --> 00:56:09.793
Not for a moment did I have
any negative thoughts. Not once.

00:56:10.071 --> 00:56:16.311
I was confident I'd score.
That morning, we never watch penalties,

00:56:16.512 --> 00:56:21.632
but after the meeting ended,
a few of us stayed. Mrma too.

00:56:22.060 --> 00:56:25.580
He showed us how Schmeichel
saves penalties.

00:56:26.820 --> 00:56:31.304
We watch. The guy dives,
a fantastic goalkeeper, normally,

00:56:31.465 --> 00:56:33.785
but he goes one way
for a minute and a half.

00:56:33.946 --> 00:56:36.812
Incredible. None of the penalties
were even close.

00:56:37.062 --> 00:56:41.422
I said that morning, if we get
a penalty, I'll strike down the middle.

00:56:41.685 --> 00:56:45.325
And then in the 120th minute,
the penalty comes. That's the mind.

00:56:45.451 --> 00:56:48.609
I don’t strike down the middle,
but the way I did.

00:56:48.741 --> 00:56:54.546
And he caught it "alive".
In the shootout it barely went in.

00:56:55.234 --> 00:57:00.500
I had it in my head.
So yeah, the mind is wild.

00:57:00.900 --> 00:57:10.140
Alright. After Denmark comes Russia,
then that trance match vs England.

00:57:10.580 --> 00:57:15.180
And the final and everything.
You were named the best player, right?

00:57:15.380 --> 00:57:21.060
Was it already then... Did you...
When did you first think

00:57:21.300 --> 00:57:29.020
that you might win
the Ballon d’Or? -Honestly? Never.

00:57:29.380 --> 00:57:34.620
Not because I didn’t believe
I deserved it,

00:57:35.540 --> 00:57:42.620
but you’re playing in the era
of two "beasts", Cristiano and Messi,

00:57:42.820 --> 00:57:48.420
no one can match them.
Goals, assists, trophies.

00:57:48.660 --> 00:57:53.500
Any way you look at it.
It never crossed my mind.

00:57:53.780 --> 00:57:59.952
For me, individual... Team trophies
are always before individual ones.

00:58:00.105 --> 00:58:05.437
Team awards ahead of individual ones.
I never even thought

00:58:06.142 --> 00:58:11.342
that I could win the Ballon d’Or,
that I could be the best and so on.

00:58:11.863 --> 00:58:16.223
But you were the best at the World Cup.
-I was the best player at the World Cup.

00:58:16.940 --> 00:58:23.882
They were there too. -One of the
happiest individual moments.

00:58:24.011 --> 00:58:26.891
Best player of the World Cup.
I was so sad because of it,

00:58:27.030 --> 00:58:31.630
because we lost the final.
I’d give anything to win the final.

00:58:32.420 --> 00:58:39.420
That fulfils me more.
But I didn’t think of the Ballon d’Or.

00:58:39.980 --> 00:58:47.740
Later I started thinking about it
when people from France Football came

00:58:48.020 --> 00:58:55.740
and said there might be a chance.
I thought OK, there’s a chance,

00:58:56.380 --> 00:59:04.980
but unlikely. You think Ronaldo
or Messi will win it. -A monopoly.

00:59:05.180 --> 00:59:08.300
They had it for 10 years. -For ten
years they just alternated.

00:59:08.580 --> 00:59:13.254
But then when the phone rang...
-What can I say.

00:59:13.434 --> 00:59:16.314
One of the most beautiful
moments of my career.

00:59:19.180 --> 00:59:22.460
Winning the Ballon d’Or.
When you see who won it

00:59:22.740 --> 00:59:32.060
and to be among them is incredible.
They told me a month before,

00:59:32.300 --> 00:59:36.420
at France Football, the director came
to Madrid and said there’s a chance,

00:59:36.660 --> 00:59:43.700
I’m in contention for the Ballon d’Or.
But they’d call only if I actually won it.

00:59:43.940 --> 00:59:48.740
Only then. They won’t call to say
I didn’t win or that I was second.

00:59:48.980 --> 00:59:56.380
They’ll call only if I win.
OK. I ask what’s the status.

00:59:56.660 --> 01:00:00.140
They say they don’t know yet,
but there’s a chance.

01:00:00.420 --> 01:00:05.900
That’s when I started imagining
how good it would be.

01:00:06.260 --> 01:00:11.980
We played Nations League in London
against England, lost 2-1.

01:00:12.180 --> 01:00:17.500
I stayed in London that night,
we had time off.

01:00:18.420 --> 01:00:25.140
When I woke around 10
in the morning, phone rings.

01:00:25.540 --> 01:00:32.300
France Football. -Come on. -I look
at the phone... -Did it hit you then? -Yes.

01:00:32.580 --> 01:00:36.100
They said they’d call.
Tears came, Vanja next to me.

01:00:36.380 --> 01:00:43.380
She says answer. I say no.
Let me calm down. Leave me a bit.

01:00:43.580 --> 01:00:48.020
You're crazy, answer.
I let it ring out and didn’t answer.

01:00:48.260 --> 01:00:51.860
Five minutes passed and then...

01:00:53.740 --> 01:00:57.460
The feeling is unreal.
Now I call them.

01:00:57.780 --> 01:01:02.140
I think they’ll say you were close,
but not this time.

01:01:02.380 --> 01:01:09.580
He says you won the Ballon d’Or.
It was... An incredible moment.

01:01:09.703 --> 01:01:11.505
An amazing feeling.

01:01:13.100 --> 01:01:16.900
The worst is you can’t
tell anyone. -How long?

01:01:19.380 --> 01:01:23.670
It was November, and the ceremony
was December 1st, something like that.

01:01:23.800 --> 01:01:26.753
Not to say the wrong date.
-Enough days to go crazy. -Two weeks.

01:01:26.777 --> 01:01:29.657
For two weeks you’re not
allowed to tell anyone.

01:01:29.897 --> 01:01:32.977
Vanja knew, and my family
kept asking…

01:01:33.137 --> 01:01:36.137
Every day someone asks you, because
people are talking about it. -Yeah.

01:01:36.337 --> 01:01:39.297
…a month before it happens,
everyone keeps asking about that.

01:01:39.497 --> 01:01:41.777
When I found out,
they asked even more.

01:01:41.977 --> 01:01:45.497
I kept saying, "I have no idea",
but inside I was dying to tell them.

01:01:45.697 --> 01:01:50.857
That day the president, Florentino,
called me and told me I’d won,

01:01:51.097 --> 01:01:54.177
even though I already knew,
they had informed him too.

01:01:54.377 --> 01:01:59.297
We talked a bit, he congratulated me.

01:02:00.937 --> 01:02:05.737
I only told Mateo,
because he’s very close to me

01:02:05.977 --> 01:02:09.537
and one of the few people
I can tell everything to.

01:02:09.817 --> 01:02:13.333
And even though I was thinking about
whether I should say it or not,

01:02:13.481 --> 01:02:15.558
I just couldn’t keep it from him.

01:02:15.743 --> 01:02:18.583
We have that kind of relationship,
I basically tell him everything.

01:02:18.679 --> 01:02:21.536
He knows everything about me,
and I know everything about him,

01:02:21.652 --> 01:02:23.292
so I told him too.

01:02:23.502 --> 01:02:34.372
Right near the end, I told my parents,
my uncle, and my close friends.

01:02:36.097 --> 01:02:39.217
Not everyone. -And Ronaldo…

01:02:40.217 --> 01:02:44.257
I wanted to leave some
room for others to come

01:02:44.657 --> 01:02:48.737
and see firsthand for themselves.
-That’s the same with the Ballon d'Or.

01:02:49.057 --> 01:02:51.097
It speaks volumes about you.

01:02:51.337 --> 01:02:57.497
That Ballon d'Or is when everyone
was simply happy that you won it.

01:02:57.737 --> 01:03:01.154
Well, yes. But of course, when
I look at it, there are always people

01:03:01.314 --> 01:03:03.865
who say I'm not Ronaldo or Messi,
and then there are some statistics...

01:03:04.022 --> 01:03:06.340
That’s today’s world.
-It wasn’t like that back then...

01:03:06.617 --> 01:03:09.377
Well, but... -No, not back then.

01:03:10.575 --> 01:03:13.677
This was unanimous, people were
genuinely happy about it.

01:03:13.885 --> 01:03:15.969
Yes, I know, I know...

01:03:16.171 --> 01:03:19.778
You know, I’m just saying there are
always people like that...

01:03:20.282 --> 01:03:24.202
But that doesn’t bother me,
I couldn’t care less.

01:03:24.494 --> 01:03:28.494
Such things do not affect me.
I know I had an incredible season,

01:03:28.695 --> 01:03:33.509
both with the national team
and with Real Madrid. I played...

01:03:34.446 --> 01:03:36.326
I don’t like talking like that,

01:03:36.911 --> 01:03:40.712
but I really played football at an
exceptional level those several years,

01:03:40.991 --> 01:03:48.337
so not just the year of the Ballon d'Or,
but the two years before it as well.

01:03:49.697 --> 01:03:53.217
Yes, but even back then, you know...

01:03:53.388 --> 01:03:56.068
The votes were overwhelmingly
in my favor,

01:03:56.377 --> 01:04:00.177
so the difference was really huge,
and it wasn’t a coincidence.

01:04:00.417 --> 01:04:06.657
6:2, you know... -It's like tennis
terminology. Yes, exactly.

01:04:07.057 --> 01:04:11.408
I don't like being pathetic,
and I know you don’t either,

01:04:12.138 --> 01:04:15.440
but I keep thinking whether I should
ask you this, but I have to.

01:04:15.589 --> 01:04:21.982
At that time, during the Russia World
Cup, that video of you and the sheep

01:04:22.207 --> 01:04:24.224
by Pavle Balenović surfaced.

01:04:26.353 --> 01:04:35.083
I thought it was so strong, I even
thought it might have been manipulated.

01:04:36.353 --> 01:04:39.313
No, no. It wasn’t.
-But it’s incredible.

01:04:39.828 --> 01:04:45.763
In those moments when the whole world
was trying to explain how Croatia,

01:04:45.977 --> 01:04:51.669
through you, was showing how a small
country could achieve something,

01:04:51.858 --> 01:04:55.218
and you were the leader of that.

01:04:58.052 --> 01:05:03.492
Everyone was trying to explain
and find reasons for it,

01:05:03.857 --> 01:05:07.577
and that photo actually
shows everything,

01:05:07.857 --> 01:05:13.234
where you see both mysticism
and control, confidence,

01:05:13.422 --> 01:05:17.062
danger, and calmness...
It’s like a match.

01:05:17.300 --> 01:05:19.804
Yes, it was. It felt like a match.

01:05:20.167 --> 01:05:25.007
You control the situation
like it’s a match. It's incredible.

01:05:25.319 --> 01:05:27.367
Did you know about that photo
before it went public?

01:05:27.537 --> 01:05:30.617
I knew about the photo. I had
seen it before. My father has it.

01:05:30.857 --> 01:05:36.767
I saw it a long time ago, but
I haven’t seen it since I was maybe

01:05:37.057 --> 01:05:43.177
10, 12 or 15 years old, doesn’t
matter... I haven’t seen it since.

01:05:44.086 --> 01:05:48.954
But then, at that moment, I actually
thought my dad had posted it somehow,

01:05:49.137 --> 01:05:52.737
but that was unimaginable, because
he never does things like that.

01:05:52.977 --> 01:05:56.457
But then, it was Pavle who posted it,

01:05:56.697 --> 01:05:59.497
and someone must have
realized it was me.

01:05:59.697 --> 01:06:03.257
The photo really brought back
memories and emotions

01:06:03.418 --> 01:06:05.538
because it’s truly incredible.

01:06:05.637 --> 01:06:09.477
I knew it existed, but I didn’t know
it would come out at that time.

01:06:09.897 --> 01:06:15.777
I used to walk there alongside goats
with my dad’s jacket,

01:06:15.977 --> 01:06:20.337
17 sizes too big for me,
always lifting it up with a stick...

01:06:21.417 --> 01:06:26.217
We did that often,
so it’s one of those photos taken

01:06:26.417 --> 01:06:30.777
when we were shooting back then,
but we often did that.

01:06:30.977 --> 01:06:35.977
That explains everything. It all makes
sense. It’s like a match situation.

01:06:36.257 --> 01:06:39.137
There’s danger,
but you’re going to solve it.

01:06:39.337 --> 01:06:42.697
You have control, concentration,
calmness, simplicity...

01:06:42.937 --> 01:06:45.417
No panic, unbelievable...

01:06:46.457 --> 01:06:51.897
Yes, and now, after the Ballon d'Or,
that you got at 33 years old,

01:06:52.137 --> 01:06:57.091
after the World Cup, it seems like
the perfect time to enjoy a little,

01:06:57.241 --> 01:06:59.333
maybe put your feet up, right?

01:06:59.572 --> 01:07:07.646
Maybe consider China or America,
a bit of relaxation, as they say.

01:07:08.417 --> 01:07:17.737
But you said no, you went full throttle
again, setting high goals for yourself.

01:07:18.217 --> 01:07:25.417
Yes, that’s me. I’m never satisfied,
I always think I can do more, better.

01:07:25.562 --> 01:07:29.442
And practically, after 2018, there were
even more incredible successes

01:07:29.675 --> 01:07:35.555
that maybe weren’t expected,
both on the national team level,

01:07:35.857 --> 01:07:38.457
in the club, and individually.

01:07:38.697 --> 01:07:43.697
It’s all because I’m not
satisfied with small things...

01:07:45.075 --> 01:07:51.589
I always want to prove myself,
and even today it’s still like that.

01:07:51.751 --> 01:07:54.253
I don’t have to prove anything to anyone,
but I want to prove myself.

01:07:54.340 --> 01:07:56.643
I want to show that I can still
be at a certain level…

01:07:56.897 --> 01:08:00.817
Every day feels like you’re
being tested. -Yeah, exactly.

01:08:01.097 --> 01:08:06.537
I started playing football out of love,
and that’s still how I see football.

01:08:06.817 --> 01:08:10.057
I never thought I’d have
what I have today.

01:08:10.257 --> 01:08:13.497
I just wanted to play football,
enjoy it, and be happy.

01:08:13.737 --> 01:08:17.057
That’s what fulfills me,
and because of that, even today,

01:08:17.257 --> 01:08:20.977
I want to play at these levels.
Because that was always my dream.

01:08:21.177 --> 01:08:30.056
I could’ve gone to other leagues,
easier leagues… -That’s the same sport.

01:08:30.238 --> 01:08:32.998
And it’s hard to win something,
no matter where you go.

01:08:33.232 --> 01:08:35.884
Yeah, but you don’t get that feeling,
it’s not the same atmosphere,

01:08:36.004 --> 01:08:39.751
it’s not the Champions League,
it’s not what I’m experiencing now in Milan.

01:08:39.868 --> 01:08:41.267
That fulfills me.

01:08:41.434 --> 01:08:46.220
Things like that, not the money…
-Money comes on its own. -Yeah.

01:08:46.350 --> 01:08:48.696
Of course you’ll look for the best
conditions you can get,

01:08:48.758 --> 01:08:50.318
but the money comes.

01:08:50.478 --> 01:08:56.212
But that was never my main goal,
and I never thought-again, I repeat,

01:08:56.492 --> 01:09:02.212
that I’d have everything I have today.
I didn’t think about that.

01:09:02.339 --> 01:09:05.539
Maybe that’s why I still last
at these levels today,

01:09:05.716 --> 01:09:11.236
because of that love… -That passion…
-The passion I have for football.

01:09:11.777 --> 01:09:16.937
That’s 100% true, absolutely solid.

01:09:17.537 --> 01:09:19.872
But it seems like you
surprised yourself a little.

01:09:20.003 --> 01:09:23.763
What you just said
is exactly my next thought,

01:09:23.924 --> 01:09:31.074
and I’d like you to comment on it.
So, the Ballon d’Or happened,

01:09:31.238 --> 01:09:36.980
the World Cup, four Champions Leagues,
and then you write a book.

01:09:37.497 --> 01:09:43.057
The book is top.
You and Robert Mateoni-great book…

01:09:44.443 --> 01:09:49.769
You were in England, where it’s completely
normal for a player during his career,

01:09:49.882 --> 01:09:52.277
if he’s a star like Rooney,
Beckham and others,

01:09:52.391 --> 01:09:54.711
to publish several books.
Five or six of them.

01:09:54.934 --> 01:09:59.534
Rooney wrote one when he was
at Everton, another one before

01:09:59.713 --> 01:10:04.426
the World Cup in Germany,
and so on… You didn’t do it that way.

01:10:04.574 --> 01:10:08.487
And second, in Europe and in our region,
a book is usually written

01:10:08.617 --> 01:10:10.737
at the peak, at the end. -Yeah.

01:10:10.977 --> 01:10:13.777
When everything is over,
so we have it all recorded.

01:10:14.017 --> 01:10:21.582
In your case it’s a paradox.
You thought that was your peak,

01:10:22.429 --> 01:10:27.789
and it turned out that your
biggest achievements came in 2018,

01:10:28.177 --> 01:10:31.497
and that was the middle of your
Real Madrid career, right? -Yeah.

01:10:31.697 --> 01:10:34.617
From 2012 that’s six years,
and then another six afterwards. -Yeah.

01:10:34.897 --> 01:10:40.657
It’s evenly split in half.
And as you said, after the World Cup,

01:10:40.857 --> 01:10:47.057
you won two Champions Leagues
and a few La Ligas. -Yeah, two or three.

01:10:47.297 --> 01:10:50.097
And with the national team,
okay it wasn’t a final,

01:10:50.274 --> 01:10:53.234
but you did win third place
and reached the Nations League final.

01:10:53.459 --> 01:10:56.579
What I want to say is…
Did you surprise yourself

01:10:56.779 --> 01:11:02.219
that it continued this intensely,
this successfully, and for this long?

01:11:04.537 --> 01:11:09.497
It’s hard for me to give an answer to that,
whether I surprised myself.

01:11:12.497 --> 01:11:14.337
I don’t know.

01:11:14.617 --> 01:11:17.505
Maybe I surprised myself
in a physical sense.

01:11:17.718 --> 01:11:20.880
I didn’t expect to be in such good
physical condition at this age.

01:11:21.049 --> 01:11:24.369
Maybe that’s the only thing
that surprised me a bit,

01:11:24.516 --> 01:11:26.981
even though I dedicated everything
to staying physically strong,

01:11:27.162 --> 01:11:30.716
as I said at the start,
with that individual trainer,

01:11:30.827 --> 01:11:33.475
when I raised my physical capacities.

01:11:33.596 --> 01:11:39.827
And you changed your diet too, right?
-I eat better, I rest more.

01:11:40.713 --> 01:11:44.313
I work on prevention,
I haven’t had many injuries…

01:11:44.623 --> 01:11:50.483
Even with everything I was doing,
I didn’t expect to be

01:11:50.701 --> 01:11:55.155
at this physical level.
-But age catches up, right? -Yeah.

01:11:55.417 --> 01:11:58.777
Maybe that’s where I did
surprise myself.

01:11:59.297 --> 01:12:03.817
But I didn’t write the book because
I thought, "Well, this is the end.

01:12:04.017 --> 01:12:06.577
Nothing else is going
to happen after this."

01:12:07.017 --> 01:12:10.817
It was simply Robi’s idea,
because we’ve had

01:12:11.017 --> 01:12:14.057
a good relationship for a long time.

01:12:14.337 --> 01:12:17.257
And he always mentioned to me
that I should write that book

01:12:17.497 --> 01:12:23.377
and that everything should be documented.
But I kept postponing it.

01:12:23.617 --> 01:12:28.497
"I’ll start tomorrow,
there’s time," and so on.

01:12:28.697 --> 01:12:32.073
But he was pretty persistent.

01:12:32.324 --> 01:12:35.689
He kept insisting, and I said,
"Okay, let’s do it."

01:12:35.906 --> 01:12:42.096
The book came out in 2019,
but not because I thought it was the end.

01:12:42.605 --> 01:12:47.405
So I wrote it, and thankfully
the book was well received.

01:12:47.747 --> 01:12:53.877
It’s just a shame that during that period
Covid appeared, so we couldn’t

01:12:54.107 --> 01:12:58.867
do a few promotions, especially
in England and other countries.

01:12:59.217 --> 01:13:02.817
But the book was well received…
-…And it stays forever.

01:13:03.057 --> 01:13:06.497
Yeah, it remains forever.
I’m proud of it in the end.

01:13:06.681 --> 01:13:11.041
Even though I needed some convincing,
once I finally decide to do something,

01:13:11.297 --> 01:13:14.937
I end up being glad later. -Yeah.
-And I’m glad about this as well.

01:13:16.377 --> 01:13:21.777
Great. We’ll talk a bit more.
You’re a perfect example of this,

01:13:22.177 --> 01:13:27.337
and I ask all my guests this,
and all of you are great in your own way,

01:13:28.017 --> 01:13:35.257
and I’m privileged to have you here.
You are, as we said, a creative player,

01:13:35.457 --> 01:13:38.217
an artist, you have a feel
for the game, technique…

01:13:38.315 --> 01:13:40.403
It’s like you have rear-view mirrors.

01:13:40.636 --> 01:13:43.356
You never know from which side
someone will attack you,

01:13:43.501 --> 01:13:46.021
you don’t even turn around,
but you feel it.

01:13:46.245 --> 01:13:52.512
But at the same time, you work
incredibly hard. You’re responsible…

01:13:55.617 --> 01:14:01.177
When you compare work and talent,
what’s the balance there,

01:14:01.377 --> 01:14:06.537
if you want to become
really successful in sports?

01:14:09.697 --> 01:14:14.926
When we were younger and part
of the youth national teams,

01:14:15.607 --> 01:14:21.207
we had coaches, instructors,
like Martin Novoselac,

01:14:21.662 --> 01:14:26.142
Ivica Grnja, Mladen Brnčić…
-Gudelj and the others…

01:14:26.302 --> 01:14:28.262
Ivan Gudelj, yes.

01:14:28.462 --> 01:14:32.942
And something Martin Novoselac
said stuck with me forever.

01:14:33.135 --> 01:14:40.135
Talent is 20%, and everything else
is hard, grueling work. Sacrifice.

01:14:43.497 --> 01:14:49.337
And at that age,
it all sounds kind of abstract,

01:14:49.577 --> 01:14:53.857
and you don’t fully understand
what he’s telling you.

01:14:54.137 --> 01:14:57.977
But at the end of the day,
I agree with that statement,

01:14:58.217 --> 01:15:03.937
that talent may be 20%,
and the rest is work.

01:15:04.177 --> 01:15:12.937
Hard work, building yourself up, sacrifice,
full focus on what you’re doing.

01:15:13.777 --> 01:15:17.657
All of that is necessary to succeed,
talent alone isn’t enough.

01:15:17.857 --> 01:15:22.022
Talent is a big plus,
but without work, talent is nothing.

01:15:22.247 --> 01:15:26.436
But you’re still born as Modrić.
-Yeah, but even then…

01:15:26.724 --> 01:15:31.404
Even Tesla wouldn’t have
been Tesla without work.

01:15:32.726 --> 01:15:36.241
Without work there’s no success,
that’s not even up for debate,

01:15:36.422 --> 01:15:39.170
but you also can’t ignore talent
and say that everyone today

01:15:39.285 --> 01:15:41.546
can do everything.
-No, of course not.

01:15:41.692 --> 01:15:44.717
You can’t become Modrić
just by training. -Of course.

01:15:45.030 --> 01:15:49.358
In my opinion… -You can only become
the best version of yourself.

01:15:50.513 --> 01:15:54.553
Of course it’s hard without talent.
There are cases where people

01:15:54.746 --> 01:15:57.786
achieved something
through work alone. -There are.

01:15:58.159 --> 01:16:01.788
But if you have enough talent,
the kind God gives you,

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:05.327
like He thankfully gave to me
and to others,

01:16:06.152 --> 01:16:09.272
I know because I lived through it…

01:16:09.590 --> 01:16:14.466
In my generation there were
unbelievably talented players,

01:16:14.648 --> 01:16:18.099
even bigger and better talents than me,
players people expected a lot from…

01:16:18.236 --> 01:16:20.146
I’m not so sure about that…

01:16:20.285 --> 01:16:25.841
At that time they expected
much more from them than from me.

01:16:26.049 --> 01:16:32.849
I know that. I’m not sure whether
that’s just people’s claims or opinions.

01:16:33.041 --> 01:16:38.081
But I knew them, I played with players
who were truly incredible.

01:16:38.422 --> 01:16:43.582
But in the end, they didn’t make it.
Whether it was because they worked less…

01:16:44.048 --> 01:16:46.107
Sometimes things
just don’t fall into place.

01:16:46.314 --> 01:16:50.317
Or maybe at a certain moment
things just didn’t align for them,

01:16:51.871 --> 01:16:54.911
but that work is extremely important, yes.

01:16:55.017 --> 01:16:57.724
And without talent it’s hard,
of course. -Yeah.

01:16:57.914 --> 01:17:03.714
But I think that percentage,
that ratio, might be even higher,

01:17:04.025 --> 01:17:09.122
but what’s certain is
that you have to work a lot.

01:17:09.293 --> 01:17:11.857
The percentage doesn’t matter.

01:17:12.039 --> 01:17:15.396
What matters is that
both things are important. -Yes.

01:17:16.821 --> 01:17:22.661
But there’s another category
that all of these people share,

01:17:23.097 --> 01:17:26.577
these people I call
champions or monsters.

01:17:26.777 --> 01:17:32.177
It’s that passion you keep mentioning
all the time, at dinner, now again.

01:17:32.377 --> 01:17:38.977
All I hear is "passion, passion."
It’s simply an obsession with it.

01:17:39.217 --> 01:17:46.057
Let me tell a story, something
that happened after a match,

01:17:48.217 --> 01:17:55.977
which shows your character perfectly.
It was after the Real-Chelsea game.

01:17:56.377 --> 01:17:59.377
A shocking match, a comeback…

01:17:59.530 --> 01:18:05.410
Chelsea go up 2-0, 3-0…
-Even 4-0, but the goal got disallowed.

01:18:05.657 --> 01:18:09.097
Exactly, even 4-0…
It was unbelievable.

01:18:09.297 --> 01:18:12.015
There were extra-time periods,
all sorts of things.

01:18:12.099 --> 01:18:14.257
The match finished really late.

01:18:14.424 --> 01:18:18.054
You got home at 2 a.m.,
maybe you didn’t even sleep. -Yeah.

01:18:18.258 --> 01:18:21.818
And the next day Atletico play City,
which I’m going to watch, but you’re not.

01:18:21.987 --> 01:18:25.945
But we’re meeting for lunch.
My friend Kenneth from Gibraltar,

01:18:26.081 --> 01:18:31.361
Leo-my son-you and me.
For lunch, not dinner. It was March,

01:18:31.617 --> 01:18:35.737
I think that’s when the quarterfinals
were played. Maybe it was April…

01:18:35.937 --> 01:18:43.177
Anyway, there were about
ten league rounds left in La Liga.

01:18:43.417 --> 01:18:47.097
You were first, but Barcelona
were always there.

01:18:47.337 --> 01:18:52.857
And Leo, my son, asks you at one moment:
"Luka, do you think you’ll finish first?"

01:18:53.097 --> 01:18:57.017
And I, who’ve known you
my whole life, I was stunned.

01:18:57.257 --> 01:19:00.337
Because you... maybe I'll get
the name of the club wrong,

01:19:00.577 --> 01:19:02.497
but you said something like:
"You know what, Leo,

01:19:02.611 --> 01:19:06.891
now we play at home against Getafe,
and Barcelona play against Sevilla.

01:19:07.053 --> 01:19:10.533
Then we play at home against Celta,
and they play away…"

01:19:10.874 --> 01:19:14.394
And you went through
eight rounds like that,

01:19:14.540 --> 01:19:17.500
who you play, who they play… -Yeah.

01:19:17.897 --> 01:19:19.937
And then you said:
"We’re going to Sevilla,

01:19:20.137 --> 01:19:22.817
and if we win there, we’re champions."

01:19:23.897 --> 01:19:28.457
This is happening in this new era,
where it’s totally normal

01:19:28.657 --> 01:19:31.777
for a player to say
he doesn’t follow football,

01:19:31.977 --> 01:19:35.097
he doesn’t watch matches,
he watches NFL and baseball instead,

01:19:35.337 --> 01:19:37.817
and football is just his job. -Yeah.

01:19:38.497 --> 01:19:44.177
But that passion and love
you have for football…

01:19:44.377 --> 01:19:46.497
That’s why I always repeat it.

01:19:46.697 --> 01:19:49.177
The love and passion I have
for football is huge.

01:19:49.417 --> 01:19:52.897
It’s my job, it’s my life,
so how am I not supposed to know

01:19:53.097 --> 01:19:58.404
who we play in six or seven rounds,
and who our biggest rival plays?

01:19:59.257 --> 01:20:02.057
So that I can know what they need,
what we need,

01:20:02.257 --> 01:20:06.697
and whether we have
a chance to be champions.

01:20:06.977 --> 01:20:12.617
I simply live football,
not just when I train

01:20:14.257 --> 01:20:17.937
and finish a session,
but also afterwards.

01:20:18.177 --> 01:20:20.657
I watch other matches,
I record other opponents

01:20:20.857 --> 01:20:23.457
that we’re going to play against…
And that’s still the same today.

01:20:23.697 --> 01:20:27.926
I don’t do it less now, it’s the same.
-You would do it for free.

01:20:28.908 --> 01:20:33.188
Of course, because I love it. That’s
what keeps me going even today.

01:20:33.577 --> 01:20:36.577
People always ask me:
"How? What’s the secret?"

01:20:36.692 --> 01:20:39.972
There’s no secret. Simply,
the love and passion I feel

01:20:40.156 --> 01:20:43.036
for football is unbelievable.

01:20:43.417 --> 01:20:47.457
Not just for the matches,
but even for ordinary training sessions.

01:20:47.601 --> 01:20:49.895
My family, even Vanja,
sometimes says to me:

01:20:50.072 --> 01:20:53.192
"How? Until when?
How do you have the energy?"

01:20:53.462 --> 01:20:55.702
It’s just my life.

01:20:56.158 --> 01:21:02.718
Someone is lucky if their career
lasts 10-15 years at a high level.

01:21:03.097 --> 01:21:05.697
For me, thank God,
it’s lasted 20 years.

01:21:05.897 --> 01:21:11.777
Next year will mark 20 years
since I joined the national team.

01:21:12.137 --> 01:21:14.871
Unbelievable. -Which is amazing.

01:21:15.257 --> 01:21:18.697
So as long as I feel
good and think clearly,

01:21:18.897 --> 01:21:22.017
I want to keep playing football.
Because I know I can’t play it

01:21:22.217 --> 01:21:25.417
until I’m 70 like some people
who do other kinds of jobs,

01:21:25.594 --> 01:21:29.674
they do what they love
for 50-60 years.

01:21:29.874 --> 01:21:32.354
Unfortunately, we don't
have that privilege.

01:21:32.562 --> 01:21:35.882
We have to find other jobs later,
and that's not easy.

01:21:36.137 --> 01:21:41.817
After the adrenaline, your schedule becomes
organized from A to Z, every single day.

01:21:41.962 --> 01:21:43.762
And you want to be important?

01:21:43.986 --> 01:21:49.272
Yes, you want to stay at some level,
to be important.

01:21:49.408 --> 01:21:51.448
And not on some margins?

01:21:51.587 --> 01:21:54.897
People think that it's about finances,
but it's not like that.

01:21:55.095 --> 01:22:01.968
You can't go fishing after that, although
there are cases like that. -There are.

01:22:02.647 --> 01:22:11.410
I respect those who make such decisions,
but it's like I just said.

01:22:12.887 --> 01:22:17.433
And then these questions annoy you:
"How long will you play?"

01:22:17.977 --> 01:22:22.472
These are not questions from
the last 2-3 years, it has been going on

01:22:24.777 --> 01:22:29.577
without exaggeration,
since 2018 or 2019.

01:22:29.897 --> 01:22:35.257
"You’re old, when will you finnish,
when will you stop?"

01:22:35.577 --> 01:22:39.657
And that motivated me.

01:22:40.097 --> 01:22:45.057
Of course, it annoys me when someone
asks me that every time.

01:22:47.057 --> 01:22:53.297
They put some prejudices on me,
but I was never swayed,

01:22:53.497 --> 01:23:03.097
nor did it matter to me what someone
said about the end of my career...

01:23:04.953 --> 01:23:09.625
And time for youth.

01:23:10.417 --> 01:23:15.264
Okay, I don’t take up anyone’s
space. I’m ready to fight.

01:23:15.450 --> 01:23:18.535
I’ve never asked for privileges
no matter what I’ve done,

01:23:18.777 --> 01:23:22.657
I don’t have to have a guaranteed
place or have to play.

01:23:22.897 --> 01:23:24.897
No, if someone is better,
let them play.

01:23:25.028 --> 01:23:29.148
I’m here to fight and prove that it’s
not like that, that I can be "the one".

01:23:29.426 --> 01:23:32.266
That’s that love and responsibility.

01:23:32.435 --> 01:23:38.452
Two years ago in Arabia,
I had an Armenian,

01:23:38.727 --> 01:23:41.167
Zelarayan, on my team.

01:23:41.312 --> 01:23:43.772
The guy is from Argentina, however,
he is originally from Armenia,

01:23:43.963 --> 01:23:46.323
but he can't play for Argentina,
only for Armenia.

01:23:46.541 --> 01:23:52.283
You called me when Armenia
and Wales played for the Euro.

01:23:52.977 --> 01:23:57.537
If Wales wins that last game,
Croatia goes to the play-offs. -Yes.

01:23:57.777 --> 01:24:00.137
We lost to Wales, right?

01:24:03.440 --> 01:24:08.137
You told me to tell Zelarayan
to give it his all.

01:24:08.337 --> 01:24:10.817
The game is in 20 days.

01:24:11.017 --> 01:24:14.297
You have the Champions League
at the same time,

01:24:14.497 --> 01:24:21.217
but you thought about that too.
You can's find that any more...

01:24:21.540 --> 01:24:24.020
But that’s how it was.
-Yes, that's how it was,

01:24:24.417 --> 01:24:29.817
you gave him the jersey and...
It was 1:1.

01:24:30.257 --> 01:24:36.257
So, football is great,
but do you follow all sports? -I do.

01:24:36.599 --> 01:24:39.590
Which one do you think he would
succeed in? In basketball, right?

01:24:39.617 --> 01:24:41.496
I think so.

01:24:41.799 --> 01:24:45.309
Maybe the problem is my height.
-What would you be there for then?

01:24:46.277 --> 01:24:50.277
But I think it’s still basketball.

01:24:51.177 --> 01:24:57.520
I like playing tennis, I've never
trained, but I'm good at it.

01:24:58.177 --> 01:25:04.257
But I still prefer basketball, because
I'm from the city of basketball, Zadar.

01:25:06.537 --> 01:25:09.897
In my childhood, when I wasn't playing
football, it was always basketball.

01:25:10.057 --> 01:25:15.257
It wasn't tennis, because tennis came
later. I'm good at several sports.

01:25:15.497 --> 01:25:18.417
But basketball always came
after football.

01:25:18.697 --> 01:25:21.532
Every time after training
we go to play basketball,

01:25:21.650 --> 01:25:24.446
because there were a lot of courts
in the neighborhoods,

01:25:24.619 --> 01:25:28.813
you look for the one that has two
on two, one on one, and you play.

01:25:28.979 --> 01:25:32.954
So, do you prefer team sports?
-Yes, I prefer team sports.

01:25:33.109 --> 01:25:40.349
I respect individual sports too,
especially tennis, but I prefer team sports.

01:25:43.377 --> 01:25:51.417
You've been to several countries and
played with different nationalities?

01:25:51.657 --> 01:25:55.617
Do you think that we from these areas,
it doesn't matter if it's Bosnian,

01:25:55.762 --> 01:26:01.882
Croat, Slovene, Serb or Macedonian,
do we have that "something special"?

01:26:02.019 --> 01:26:04.219
If we have that, what is it?

01:26:06.417 --> 01:26:10.537
Well, I think we have
"something special".

01:26:12.177 --> 01:26:14.857
And what is that "special"?

01:26:15.057 --> 01:26:20.697
Character! We are fighters,
we never give up.

01:26:20.897 --> 01:26:28.457
Maybe that sets us apart from others
in this area. I don't know...

01:26:28.697 --> 01:26:32.817
But I think we have "something special".
It's hard for me to answer.

01:26:32.977 --> 01:26:35.937
Maybe you know it better?

01:26:36.177 --> 01:26:39.097
The conditions are not ideal
and we have to fight.

01:26:39.337 --> 01:26:42.697
Well, that could be it, but...
-You don't have 100 fields. -Yes...

01:26:42.937 --> 01:26:46.657
But we didn't have better conditions
so we would know what it's like.

01:26:46.897 --> 01:26:52.017
Maybe if we had better conditions,
we wouldn't be so good?

01:26:52.257 --> 01:26:55.777
How do I know? -Well, we certainly
wouldn't be better. -You think so?

01:26:56.017 --> 01:26:59.373
I’m one hundred percent
convinced of that.

01:26:59.541 --> 01:27:02.607
If everything was provided for you,
if you had a hundred fields...

01:27:02.757 --> 01:27:05.931
When you were little, there was
only one ball and one playground.

01:27:06.065 --> 01:27:08.427
You had to wait,
fight with your elders or win.

01:27:08.613 --> 01:27:11.354
That's possible, but we didn't have
better to know what was better...

01:27:12.664 --> 01:27:17.330
Maybe it would have been better,
or maybe it wouldn't have been.

01:27:17.544 --> 01:27:25.548
True. -It's pointless to discuss it...
-That's true, 100%...

01:27:26.018 --> 01:27:28.595
Growing up was tough...

01:27:29.979 --> 01:27:38.158
We didn't have much and
that made us special.

01:27:38.357 --> 01:27:40.353
And tougher. -Yes.
-That's harder.

01:27:40.497 --> 01:27:45.244
It’s harder to succeed, easier to give up.
And say: "I can't!"

01:27:45.463 --> 01:27:48.743
When there's no hot water,
I don't want to take a cold shower.

01:27:48.858 --> 01:27:51.158
I don’t want to train anymore.
It's harder...

01:27:51.343 --> 01:27:54.955
But when the challenges
and difficulties are over,

01:27:55.191 --> 01:27:58.511
then that success is wonderful.
-Yes, it’s a special feeling.

01:27:58.648 --> 01:28:02.288
Yes, you know that you deserved it
and that nobody gave you anything.

01:28:03.216 --> 01:28:05.776
You're an ideal example,

01:28:05.952 --> 01:28:10.632
because your career at the top level
has lasted 20 years.

01:28:10.953 --> 01:28:13.673
Football has changed significantly.

01:28:13.842 --> 01:28:16.762
I think it has changed more
in the last ten years

01:28:16.884 --> 01:28:19.084
than in the previous fifty years,

01:28:19.223 --> 01:28:22.009
like the world itself, mobile phones
and everything...

01:28:22.222 --> 01:28:25.572
How do you compare it,
where do you see its changes?

01:28:26.018 --> 01:28:32.658
Do you like this new positional
football more?

01:28:32.996 --> 01:28:38.814
A lot of people are going back to
the romantic times, to the old days.

01:28:42.003 --> 01:28:45.041
Parents told us that it was
better before.

01:28:45.441 --> 01:28:49.201
You are the protagonist,
you were here and there.

01:28:49.497 --> 01:28:55.537
No need to be jealous? -Yes. -You were
at the top level then and now.

01:28:55.977 --> 01:28:58.817
Every time has its advantages.

01:28:59.057 --> 01:29:04.257
Sometimes I like to go back to
that past and say that it was good.

01:29:04.457 --> 01:29:09.617
But every time has its advantages
and disadvantages.

01:29:10.137 --> 01:29:15.177
Football is still special to me,
just like it is today.

01:29:15.377 --> 01:29:21.756
Maybe there are more matches today,
but they are accessible.

01:29:21.920 --> 01:29:25.497
And they are watched more,
you can watch a match every day.

01:29:25.657 --> 01:29:27.657
But it wasn't like that before.

01:29:27.810 --> 01:29:32.610
You could watch one or two games
during the weekend. -That's right.

01:29:32.763 --> 01:29:34.896
Or in the meantime, one match.

01:29:35.060 --> 01:29:37.685
And everyone could hardly
wait to watch that game.

01:29:37.857 --> 01:29:40.537
And today, every game is available.

01:29:40.695 --> 01:29:46.170
Even in some other countries,
you can watch it if you want.

01:29:46.377 --> 01:29:49.137
And that's the difference.

01:29:49.417 --> 01:29:55.737
But as for football, I had a good time
at that time, but also now.

01:29:56.497 --> 01:30:00.697
I enjoy football and it's a pleasure
for me to watch it.

01:30:00.937 --> 01:30:05.337
Just as it was a pleasure for me to
watch it before, just as I play it now.

01:30:05.537 --> 01:30:08.417
Nothing has changed
in that regard. -Yes.

01:30:08.617 --> 01:30:14.657
Every time brings good
and less good things.

01:30:14.857 --> 01:30:17.777
How do you view these new generations?

01:30:18.097 --> 01:30:23.657
Janica recently said in an interview
that she doesn't know

01:30:24.337 --> 01:30:31.017
if she would succeed if she
had to start in these new times.

01:30:31.777 --> 01:30:36.057
Everything is under supervision,
everything is pressurised...

01:30:36.257 --> 01:30:40.177
And those social networks...
Every step is under surveillance.

01:30:40.377 --> 01:30:46.218
Is it harder for the players now
or not? -Yes, it is, it is much harder.

01:30:46.538 --> 01:30:52.138
Before, you could go out more relaxed,
take a walk and have a good time,

01:30:52.457 --> 01:30:58.337
without thinking whether someone
will take a photograph of you

01:30:58.506 --> 01:31:00.946
or whether you will be
in the newspapers.

01:31:01.193 --> 01:31:04.633
Will I do something?

01:31:05.937 --> 01:31:12.876
But today, whatever you do,
it is immediately published in the media.

01:31:13.509 --> 01:31:20.462
I don't like that, but simply, we live
in such times where social networks

01:31:20.937 --> 01:31:25.457
have become very important
and essential.

01:31:26.337 --> 01:31:33.837
Honestly, I don't like that, but we
have to follow trends and adapt.

01:31:34.470 --> 01:31:40.977
That's true, but I used to have
a better time. And I was more relaxed.

01:31:41.177 --> 01:31:47.057
I could talk to my friends, but now
everyone has a phone in their hand.

01:31:47.257 --> 01:31:52.897
When they finish the match, first thing
the players do is take the phone.

01:31:53.097 --> 01:31:56.177
Right away, yes. -That's right,
we don't talk about the match

01:31:56.377 --> 01:31:59.811
or about what could have been better.
What was done well and what was not.

01:32:00.010 --> 01:32:03.061
It used to be like that until
there were no telephones.

01:32:03.248 --> 01:32:06.256
We talked about the match,
about what you were doing.

01:32:06.449 --> 01:32:09.912
And it's a difference. That's why
earlier it was surely more beautiful,

01:32:10.143 --> 01:32:15.053
but now it just is. We have to adapt.
Progress is being made...

01:32:15.897 --> 01:32:22.072
You don't seem to belong to this time,
as they used to say…

01:32:24.090 --> 01:32:29.134
"A six or an eight, it's a shame,
he left for this or that."

01:32:29.454 --> 01:32:36.064
That's what they say now, that there are
no such responsible players.

01:32:36.837 --> 01:32:40.198
You are special and that
should be emphasized.

01:32:40.447 --> 01:32:43.807
That's why I called you
when you beat Napoli,

01:32:44.026 --> 01:32:46.252
two or three weeks ago
with a score of 2:1

01:32:46.694 --> 01:32:51.612
So, a red card, a penalty and 30 minutes
to the end, not 5. -And more.

01:32:52.395 --> 01:32:57.089
I have to tell you, if it weren't for you,

01:32:57.325 --> 01:33:00.685
I feel that they would have lost
with a score of 3:2.

01:33:00.917 --> 01:33:05.277
Regardless of whether you cleared
2 goals from the line

01:33:05.657 --> 01:33:13.017
or created 6 chances for your forward.
Simply, you have that responsibility.

01:33:13.457 --> 01:33:16.257
I know that as a coach,
but I was also a player...

01:33:16.497 --> 01:33:21.617
There is a player's responsibility
and a coach's responsibility.

01:33:21.817 --> 01:33:23.977
Both want to win.

01:33:24.297 --> 01:33:26.737
A player wants to win,

01:33:26.977 --> 01:33:30.617
because he has a certain
limit of sacrifice to make that.

01:33:31.097 --> 01:33:37.177
And the coach has maximum
responsibility for everything.

01:33:37.937 --> 01:33:42.737
You are the person on the field
who leads and suffers,

01:33:42.937 --> 01:33:51.297
as if he is the only one responsible
for a possible defeat. -That's right.

01:33:53.617 --> 01:33:57.737
But that's not there anymore today.
There used to be a lot more of that.

01:33:58.017 --> 01:34:00.577
Not just Roy Keane
and players like that...

01:34:02.417 --> 01:34:05.417
That was somehow the standard.

01:34:05.737 --> 01:34:16.177
Today that's gone. -Yes. -100%.
When you look at your path,

01:34:17.697 --> 01:34:21.697
which you mentioned during
the conversation,

01:34:21.937 --> 01:34:24.537
and everything you've been through,

01:34:24.777 --> 01:34:30.498
if you had to go through it again,
would you be scared?

01:34:30.783 --> 01:34:35.666
You would simply think
it was a movie. It's hard.

01:34:35.992 --> 01:34:38.894
Yes, it's hard, but it's sweet.

01:34:39.457 --> 01:34:43.937
And I wouldn't change anything,
if I don’t know what will happen.

01:34:44.177 --> 01:34:49.657
I would like to go through this same
path again that I have. -Sure.

01:34:50.657 --> 01:34:54.681
I am proud and happy...
-And you should be.

01:34:54.877 --> 01:34:58.978
... about what I have achieved so far
and the way I have achieved it.

01:34:59.777 --> 01:35:04.217
With the people who helped
me on that path.

01:35:04.497 --> 01:35:09.217
Of course, you can't do it all alone.
You need coaches, parents,

01:35:09.457 --> 01:35:17.249
wife and fans. Some contributed
less, some more...

01:35:18.097 --> 01:35:24.657
I am grateful for that help
and for everything

01:35:25.297 --> 01:35:29.297
they gave for me on that path.

01:35:29.897 --> 01:35:34.457
So I am proud and happy and I really
wouldn't change anything.

01:35:35.257 --> 01:35:38.044
Do you think you would
have succeeded like this

01:35:38.226 --> 01:35:40.786
if you had been born 100 meters
from the Bernabeu?

01:35:41.198 --> 01:35:46.278
It's hard to know, but knowing
myself and my character,

01:35:47.097 --> 01:35:51.337
and if I had been born
next to the Bernabeu,

01:35:51.577 --> 01:35:55.457
I think I would have done something.
Regardless the difference.

01:35:55.697 --> 01:36:00.937
I simply wanted to succeed.
I had my dreams, my desires

01:36:01.217 --> 01:36:08.377
and I followed them. I didn't let
anything on that path stop me.

01:36:08.657 --> 01:36:14.017
Nor for anyone to tell me that
I can't do it. And to give up...

01:36:14.257 --> 01:36:18.897
No, I believed in myself
and blindly followed my path.

01:36:19.097 --> 01:36:21.057
That's right. Yes. -That's it.

01:36:21.297 --> 01:36:24.977
And you had the support of your family?
-And that's the most important support.

01:36:25.217 --> 01:36:28.657
In those moments...
-Some things come together.

01:36:28.897 --> 01:36:33.217
Which ones you provoke.
Nothing is impossible without the other.

01:36:33.478 --> 01:36:36.953
But you have to believe in yourself.

01:36:37.211 --> 01:36:47.377
Today it's popular for everyone
to criticize and drag you down.

01:36:48.181 --> 01:36:50.661
They don't want you to succeed.

01:36:53.745 --> 01:37:01.979
If you accept that thinking and if it
destabilizes you, then it's difficult.

01:37:02.768 --> 01:37:08.677
That's why you need to move away
from those thoughts, not listen to them.

01:37:09.132 --> 01:37:19.370
Especially if the prevailing opinion
is not your own opinion of yourself.

01:37:19.513 --> 01:37:24.221
But it’s hard today to be under
the influence of social media.

01:37:24.468 --> 01:37:27.948
Yes, it's much harder, because
you read every comment.

01:37:28.094 --> 01:37:30.774
But... you just have to be strong.

01:37:30.998 --> 01:37:33.638
You have to be stronger than
that and parents have to talk

01:37:33.745 --> 01:37:35.785
to their children too. -Yes.

01:37:35.979 --> 01:37:39.059
You have three children?

01:37:41.177 --> 01:37:43.297
Are they all in sports?

01:37:44.137 --> 01:37:50.497
The younger one, Sofi, no,
but she practices another sport,

01:37:50.709 --> 01:37:55.874
ballet and rhythmic gymnastics…
But she is still young.

01:37:56.068 --> 01:38:00.366
Ema is into soccer
and she is excellent.

01:38:00.489 --> 01:38:02.655
Now how much she wants to continue...

01:38:02.810 --> 01:38:05.100
For now she is interested
in it and she likes it.

01:38:06.512 --> 01:38:09.163
And Ivano too, he likes soccer.

01:38:09.371 --> 01:38:14.905
At first he wasn't that interested,
when I forced him...

01:38:16.173 --> 01:38:20.693
Later I realized that I shouldn't do that.
He should decide what he wants.

01:38:20.814 --> 01:38:25.894
The most important thing for me is that
they are happy, whatever they do.

01:38:26.095 --> 01:38:29.415
To be happy in sports
or any other profession,

01:38:29.568 --> 01:38:32.171
just that they are happy
and that they enjoy it.

01:38:32.279 --> 01:38:35.319
And that they give their best
in whatever they do.

01:38:35.503 --> 01:38:37.983
And not that they do something halfway.

01:38:38.106 --> 01:38:42.249
I don't like that, it irritates me,
when something is done halfway.

01:38:42.572 --> 01:38:52.132
No matter what it is. So... I don't force
them, I let them choose.

01:38:52.337 --> 01:38:56.057
I'm here to support them.

01:38:57.877 --> 01:39:02.385
They have to be happy and enjoy it.
-Will you support them professionally?

01:39:02.572 --> 01:39:06.777
Of course. Whatever they choose,
I'm here to support them.

01:39:07.017 --> 01:39:10.697
But when they choose something,
they have to give their best in it,

01:39:10.897 --> 01:39:15.337
and not do it halfway...
And that's the only thing I ask of them.

01:39:15.522 --> 01:39:20.202
And the last question,
how do you and Vanja deal

01:39:20.377 --> 01:39:25.617
with this problem of mobile phones,
social networks, this scourge?

01:39:26.161 --> 01:39:28.481
It's hard, it's not easy.

01:39:31.737 --> 01:39:36.457
Everyone around them has had
phones since they were young.

01:39:37.057 --> 01:39:41.694
Until they were a little older,
they didn’t have a mobile phone.

01:39:41.785 --> 01:39:43.465
And then every day they asked,

01:39:43.619 --> 01:39:46.046
"Why don't we have one
and others have one?"

01:39:46.186 --> 01:39:52.066
It wasn't easy to deal with it,
but we managed to some extent.

01:39:52.299 --> 01:39:56.019
We didn't give them mobile phones
until they were a little older.

01:39:56.150 --> 01:40:01.030
We try to keep it to a minimum
when they have weekly classes.

01:40:01.129 --> 01:40:04.326
Or they only have their phones
for an hour after school.

01:40:04.537 --> 01:40:07.850
On weekends, we allow them
to use their phones a little longer,

01:40:08.001 --> 01:40:11.467
because you can't completely
cut them off from it.

01:40:11.653 --> 01:40:14.553
They will be isolated from
society then. -Isolated, yes.

01:40:14.776 --> 01:40:17.796
When you ask them why they're
constantly on their mobile phones,

01:40:17.960 --> 01:40:20.760
they say, "You're constantly
on your mobile phone too."

01:40:22.408 --> 01:40:24.405
And what should you tell them?

01:40:24.570 --> 01:40:31.233
They are good, they listen, but we
still can't completely isolate them.

01:40:31.491 --> 01:40:36.280
It's a daily struggle.
-It's a daily struggle, conversations...

01:40:36.817 --> 01:40:40.937
It's not easy, but we try
to lead them on the right path.

01:40:41.114 --> 01:40:45.354
To give them the right values,
like my parents did for me.

01:40:45.519 --> 01:40:49.519
That they be humble
and respect their elders.

01:40:51.097 --> 01:40:58.017
That's the most important thing for me.
That they have those right values.

01:40:58.617 --> 01:41:04.337
My Luka, well done, congratulations!
-Thank you, the pleasure is mine.

